WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:13.773 align:middle line:90%


00:00:13.773 --> 00:00:15.064 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA GARR: Hello and welcome.

00:00:15.064 --> 00:00:15.910 align:middle line:90%
I'm Lisa Garr.

00:00:15.910 --> 00:00:18.100 align:middle line:84%
With all of the demands
on your time these days,

00:00:18.100 --> 00:00:20.820 align:middle line:84%
between work and family
and relationships

00:00:20.820 --> 00:00:24.075 align:middle line:84%
and a constant demand to
answer your email or your texts

00:00:24.075 --> 00:00:25.990 align:middle line:84%
all day, are you
feeling that you're

00:00:25.990 --> 00:00:28.100 align:middle line:84%
getting tugged in several
different directions?

00:00:28.100 --> 00:00:30.650 align:middle line:84%
Do you think that a
state of enlightenment

00:00:30.650 --> 00:00:32.990 align:middle line:84%
is for other people
who have time

00:00:32.990 --> 00:00:34.115 align:middle line:90%
for things like meditation?

00:00:34.115 --> 00:00:35.160 align:middle line:90%


00:00:35.160 --> 00:00:38.430 align:middle line:84%
Joining me today is spiritual
teacher and cultural visionary,

00:00:38.430 --> 00:00:39.330 align:middle line:90%
Andrew Cohen.

00:00:39.330 --> 00:00:42.220 align:middle line:84%
And he's here to talk about
his book, "Evolutionary

00:00:42.220 --> 00:00:46.230 align:middle line:84%
Enlightenment: A New Path
to Spiritual Awakening"

00:00:46.230 --> 00:00:49.430 align:middle line:84%
and how to achieve practical
spirituality without feeling

00:00:49.430 --> 00:00:51.310 align:middle line:84%
like you are being
tugged and split

00:00:51.310 --> 00:00:52.950 align:middle line:90%
in several different directions.

00:00:52.950 --> 00:00:53.910 align:middle line:90%
Welcome to the show.

00:00:53.910 --> 00:00:55.180 align:middle line:90%
Thank you for joining me.

00:00:55.180 --> 00:00:55.760 align:middle line:90%
>>ANDREW COHEN: Thank you, Lisa.

00:00:55.760 --> 00:00:56.800 align:middle line:90%
I'm thrilled to be with you.

00:00:56.800 --> 00:00:58.716 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I'm glad you're
with me because you're

00:00:58.716 --> 00:01:00.450 align:middle line:84%
going to bring
this whole concept

00:01:00.450 --> 00:01:03.640 align:middle line:84%
and topic of enlightenment
to a level that

00:01:03.640 --> 00:01:05.840 align:middle line:84%
is practical for
people like me, who

00:01:05.840 --> 00:01:08.040 align:middle line:84%
tend to live a little
bit of a busy life.

00:01:08.040 --> 00:01:09.915 align:middle line:84%
What is your perspective
of enlightenment?

00:01:09.915 --> 00:01:10.934 align:middle line:90%


00:01:10.934 --> 00:01:12.600 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: My perspective
of enlightenment

00:01:12.600 --> 00:01:13.530 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's a big
question, I know.

00:01:13.530 --> 00:01:15.620 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: It's a very big
question to start with.

00:01:15.620 --> 00:01:18.610 align:middle line:84%
Well, I think probably
the word means

00:01:18.610 --> 00:01:21.090 align:middle line:84%
many things in many
different circumstances.

00:01:21.090 --> 00:01:23.990 align:middle line:84%
But I suppose, just to
begin our conversation,

00:01:23.990 --> 00:01:31.730 align:middle line:84%
it means discovering, at an
experiential level, a sense

00:01:31.730 --> 00:01:36.030 align:middle line:84%
of ultimacy, discovering
a non-relative or absolute

00:01:36.030 --> 00:01:39.880 align:middle line:84%
dimension or position in
relationship to life that

00:01:39.880 --> 00:01:43.860 align:middle line:84%
frees one from existential
doubt and existential fear.

00:01:43.860 --> 00:01:49.160 align:middle line:84%
Because a lot of us are
consciously and unconsciously

00:01:49.160 --> 00:01:50.910 align:middle line:84%
confused, knowingly
or unknowingly,

00:01:50.910 --> 00:01:53.510 align:middle line:84%
about what's the point
of this experience?

00:01:53.510 --> 00:01:54.650 align:middle line:90%
Why am I here?

00:01:54.650 --> 00:01:55.550 align:middle line:90%
Is life good?

00:01:55.550 --> 00:01:57.630 align:middle line:90%


00:01:57.630 --> 00:01:59.850 align:middle line:84%
So experiences like
these really answer

00:01:59.850 --> 00:02:03.400 align:middle line:84%
these fundamental
existential questions

00:02:03.400 --> 00:02:04.750 align:middle line:90%
that all human beings have.

00:02:04.750 --> 00:02:07.380 align:middle line:84%
For some people they're more
conscious; for other people

00:02:07.380 --> 00:02:08.720 align:middle line:90%
they're less unconscious.

00:02:08.720 --> 00:02:13.250 align:middle line:84%
And essentially it
removes all doubt

00:02:13.250 --> 00:02:15.710 align:middle line:84%
about whether life is
good and whether I really

00:02:15.710 --> 00:02:17.180 align:middle line:90%
want to be here.

00:02:17.180 --> 00:02:19.740 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: How did you get
started on this entire path

00:02:19.740 --> 00:02:23.040 align:middle line:84%
of your journey, your
spiritual journey?

00:02:23.040 --> 00:02:25.690 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, I was brought up
in a secular Jewish household

00:02:25.690 --> 00:02:28.760 align:middle line:84%
in New York, so I
had no notion of God

00:02:28.760 --> 00:02:31.710 align:middle line:84%
or spirit or really
anything higher.

00:02:31.710 --> 00:02:33.740 align:middle line:84%
And then when I
was 16 years old,

00:02:33.740 --> 00:02:35.980 align:middle line:84%
I was living in Rome in
Italy with my mother.

00:02:35.980 --> 00:02:38.000 align:middle line:84%
And we were sitting up
late one night having

00:02:38.000 --> 00:02:40.420 align:middle line:84%
a conversation--and I don't
remember what we were talking

00:02:40.420 --> 00:02:43.500 align:middle line:84%
about--but for no
particular reason,

00:02:43.500 --> 00:02:47.365 align:middle line:84%
the doors of perception opened,
and I had an experience.

00:02:47.365 --> 00:02:48.410 align:middle line:90%


00:02:48.410 --> 00:02:50.720 align:middle line:84%
I had what's called a
transrational experience.

00:02:50.720 --> 00:02:53.560 align:middle line:84%
In other words, it's difficult
to understand rationally,

00:02:53.560 --> 00:02:54.650 align:middle line:90%
but this is what happened.

00:02:54.650 --> 00:02:56.460 align:middle line:84%
So the doors of
perception opened,

00:02:56.460 --> 00:02:59.935 align:middle line:84%
and I became aware
of beginninglessness

00:02:59.935 --> 00:03:03.820 align:middle line:84%
and endlessness, that which had
no beginning and no end, right?

00:03:03.820 --> 00:03:06.667 align:middle line:84%
All sense of boundaries and all
sense of limitation fell away.

00:03:06.667 --> 00:03:09.000 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Was it different than
the prior moments you were

00:03:09.000 --> 00:03:09.480 align:middle line:90%
experiencing--

00:03:09.480 --> 00:03:10.190 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: Completely different.

00:03:10.190 --> 00:03:11.380 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: --as a teenager?

00:03:11.380 --> 00:03:12.730 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: Completely different.

00:03:12.730 --> 00:03:15.790 align:middle line:84%
It would be like living
in a small little cabin

00:03:15.790 --> 00:03:18.580 align:middle line:84%
and opening the door and
falling into infinite space.

00:03:18.580 --> 00:03:19.630 align:middle line:90%


00:03:19.630 --> 00:03:20.130 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:03:20.130 --> 00:03:23.370 align:middle line:84%
And it was a cosmic
cracking of consciousness.

00:03:23.370 --> 00:03:25.140 align:middle line:90%


00:03:25.140 --> 00:03:31.000 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, I was literally
aware of the infinite.

00:03:31.000 --> 00:03:32.180 align:middle line:90%
It was more tangible.

00:03:32.180 --> 00:03:34.670 align:middle line:84%
It was the awareness
of the infinite,

00:03:34.670 --> 00:03:37.810 align:middle line:84%
or beginninglessness and
endlessness was more tangible,

00:03:37.810 --> 00:03:40.470 align:middle line:84%
was more real in
those few moments

00:03:40.470 --> 00:03:42.600 align:middle line:84%
than anything else I'd ever
experienced in my life.

00:03:42.600 --> 00:03:44.636 align:middle line:84%
And that, of course, is
what makes experiences

00:03:44.636 --> 00:03:45.760 align:middle line:90%
like that so extraordinary.

00:03:45.760 --> 00:03:47.780 align:middle line:90%


00:03:47.780 --> 00:03:51.470 align:middle line:84%
There was a quality
of this infiniteness

00:03:51.470 --> 00:03:54.760 align:middle line:90%
that was of overwhelming love.

00:03:54.760 --> 00:03:56.890 align:middle line:84%
But it was a kind
of love that it's

00:03:56.890 --> 00:04:01.140 align:middle line:84%
hard to relate to anything that
we normally relate to that word

00:04:01.140 --> 00:04:03.270 align:middle line:84%
because it was
completely overwhelming.

00:04:03.270 --> 00:04:04.730 align:middle line:90%


00:04:04.730 --> 00:04:05.750 align:middle line:90%
It was breathtaking.

00:04:05.750 --> 00:04:06.800 align:middle line:90%
It was crushing.

00:04:06.800 --> 00:04:11.460 align:middle line:84%
And it almost felt like
if the intensity of what

00:04:11.460 --> 00:04:13.627 align:middle line:84%
I was experiencing didn't
stop, I might not make it.

00:04:13.627 --> 00:04:14.460 align:middle line:90%
I might not survive.

00:04:14.460 --> 00:04:15.835 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that's
how strong it was.

00:04:15.835 --> 00:04:18.690 align:middle line:84%
I was in a state of awe, and
I was in a state of wonder.

00:04:18.690 --> 00:04:20.060 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What did your mother do?

00:04:20.060 --> 00:04:22.297 align:middle line:84%
Did she see this
happening in your face?

00:04:22.297 --> 00:04:22.880 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: Yeah.

00:04:22.880 --> 00:04:24.891 align:middle line:84%
Well, yeah, tears were
streaming down my face.

00:04:24.891 --> 00:04:26.640 align:middle line:84%
But I wasn't even
crying, I was in a state

00:04:26.640 --> 00:04:30.710 align:middle line:84%
of awe at the splendor
and the glory of it all.

00:04:30.710 --> 00:04:33.410 align:middle line:90%


00:04:33.410 --> 00:04:35.560 align:middle line:84%
She didn't really know
what was happening to me.

00:04:35.560 --> 00:04:37.220 align:middle line:84%
We were in two
different dimensions.

00:04:37.220 --> 00:04:39.640 align:middle line:84%
Our physical bodies were
sitting in the same room,

00:04:39.640 --> 00:04:43.510 align:middle line:84%
but we were in two completely
different dimensions

00:04:43.510 --> 00:04:44.980 align:middle line:90%
of existence.

00:04:44.980 --> 00:04:48.170 align:middle line:84%
And I remember at that
time that I'd recently

00:04:48.170 --> 00:04:50.370 align:middle line:84%
seen a documentary
about Buddhism.

00:04:50.370 --> 00:04:53.579 align:middle line:84%
And in that documentary, there
was an image of a huge statue

00:04:53.579 --> 00:04:55.370 align:middle line:84%
somewhere in the jungles
of Southeast Asia,

00:04:55.370 --> 00:04:57.940 align:middle line:84%
and there were hundreds
of monks prostrating

00:04:57.940 --> 00:05:00.190 align:middle line:84%
before this enormous
Buddha statue.

00:05:00.190 --> 00:05:02.730 align:middle line:84%
But because I hadn't had
any experiences like this,

00:05:02.730 --> 00:05:05.350 align:middle line:84%
I didn't understand why
any human being would

00:05:05.350 --> 00:05:07.670 align:middle line:90%
bow down and prostrate before--

00:05:07.670 --> 00:05:08.470 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: A statue.

00:05:08.470 --> 00:05:09.210 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: --a statute.

00:05:09.210 --> 00:05:11.043 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't even know
why a human being would

00:05:11.043 --> 00:05:12.892 align:middle line:84%
want to prostrate
before anything.

00:05:12.892 --> 00:05:14.600 align:middle line:84%
And I remember in that
moment, I suddenly

00:05:14.600 --> 00:05:17.500 align:middle line:84%
understood what was
the sentiment that

00:05:17.500 --> 00:05:20.490 align:middle line:84%
was being expressed when
those monks were bowing down

00:05:20.490 --> 00:05:23.920 align:middle line:90%
before the image of Lord Buddha.

00:05:23.920 --> 00:05:24.850 align:middle line:90%
And--

00:05:24.850 --> 00:05:27.950 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Did that cause you to
want to go to those regions

00:05:27.950 --> 00:05:29.510 align:middle line:90%
and find out more about it?

00:05:29.510 --> 00:05:31.080 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: Well, not then.

00:05:31.080 --> 00:05:35.200 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I didn't really know
what it was that was happening.

00:05:35.200 --> 00:05:38.150 align:middle line:84%
I just knew that in
those few moments--

00:05:38.150 --> 00:05:39.880 align:middle line:84%
I don't exactly know
how long it lasted--

00:05:39.880 --> 00:05:44.180 align:middle line:84%
I had been more in touch with
reality, more awake, more alive

00:05:44.180 --> 00:05:47.260 align:middle line:84%
than I had been in
all of my 16 years.

00:05:47.260 --> 00:05:51.530 align:middle line:84%
And so this made a very deep and
profound impression on my soul.

00:05:51.530 --> 00:05:53.650 align:middle line:84%
But at that time, I
had other interests.

00:05:53.650 --> 00:05:54.824 align:middle line:90%


00:05:54.824 --> 00:05:56.115 align:middle line:90%
I wanted to be a jazz musician.

00:05:56.115 --> 00:05:56.667 align:middle line:90%


00:05:56.667 --> 00:05:59.000 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't really know what
to do with the experience.

00:05:59.000 --> 00:06:00.625 align:middle line:84%
I told people about
it, and most people

00:06:00.625 --> 00:06:04.820 align:middle line:84%
didn't have any idea really
what it meant or what it was.

00:06:04.820 --> 00:06:07.490 align:middle line:90%


00:06:07.490 --> 00:06:08.440 align:middle line:90%
It was interesting.

00:06:08.440 --> 00:06:11.920 align:middle line:84%
At the end of this experience,
I received a message.

00:06:11.920 --> 00:06:14.710 align:middle line:84%
And I know this sounds like
a strange thing to say,

00:06:14.710 --> 00:06:19.390 align:middle line:84%
but what it was was, if you give
your life to me and me alone,

00:06:19.390 --> 00:06:20.440 align:middle line:90%
you have nothing to fear.

00:06:20.440 --> 00:06:21.647 align:middle line:90%


00:06:21.647 --> 00:06:22.980 align:middle line:90%
And I didn't know what it meant.

00:06:22.980 --> 00:06:24.830 align:middle line:84%
And the implication
was that if I

00:06:24.830 --> 00:06:29.220 align:middle line:84%
didn't follow this
invitation from the unknown,

00:06:29.220 --> 00:06:31.235 align:middle line:84%
so to speak, that I was
going to be in trouble,

00:06:31.235 --> 00:06:33.160 align:middle line:84%
that I was going to
have a hard time.

00:06:33.160 --> 00:06:36.330 align:middle line:84%
And so I went on to pursue
my interest in music.

00:06:36.330 --> 00:06:37.214 align:middle line:90%
And when I was--

00:06:37.214 --> 00:06:39.630 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Did you pay attention
to that message at the time,

00:06:39.630 --> 00:06:41.020 align:middle line:84%
or just ignore it because you
didn't know what to do with it?

00:06:41.020 --> 00:06:42.811 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: I just was
aware that it happened.

00:06:42.811 --> 00:06:45.120 align:middle line:84%
But you see, Lisa, I
didn't have any context

00:06:45.120 --> 00:06:47.536 align:middle line:84%
in order to be able to relate
to it or know what it meant.

00:06:47.536 --> 00:06:50.470 align:middle line:84%
I hadn't been interested
in these matters before.

00:06:50.470 --> 00:06:52.865 align:middle line:84%
It was like suddenly
diving deep into the ocean

00:06:52.865 --> 00:06:54.820 align:middle line:84%
after not even knowing
that the ocean existed.

00:06:54.820 --> 00:06:56.570 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Being in the
desert, right, right?

00:06:56.570 --> 00:06:58.861 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Oh yeah, I didn't
even know the ocean existed.

00:06:58.861 --> 00:07:00.620 align:middle line:84%
So it was a powerful
awakening experience.

00:07:00.620 --> 00:07:03.552 align:middle line:84%
But the thing is, when
the experience was over,

00:07:03.552 --> 00:07:05.800 align:middle line:84%
I didn't really know
what to do with it.

00:07:05.800 --> 00:07:08.490 align:middle line:84%
But then when I was
in my early 20s,

00:07:08.490 --> 00:07:11.450 align:middle line:84%
I began to be haunted
by this event.

00:07:11.450 --> 00:07:13.100 align:middle line:90%


00:07:13.100 --> 00:07:16.170 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it was a
difficult time in my-- I

00:07:16.170 --> 00:07:17.670 align:middle line:84%
was having, as a
young adult, things

00:07:17.670 --> 00:07:19.128 align:middle line:84%
weren't going very
well in my life.

00:07:19.128 --> 00:07:21.480 align:middle line:84%
But I was being haunted
by this experience,

00:07:21.480 --> 00:07:24.430 align:middle line:84%
and there was a sense
that this was my calling.

00:07:24.430 --> 00:07:26.280 align:middle line:84%
So at a certain
point when I was 22,

00:07:26.280 --> 00:07:27.696 align:middle line:84%
I made up my mind
that I was going

00:07:27.696 --> 00:07:32.240 align:middle line:84%
to devote my life to
the rediscovery of what

00:07:32.240 --> 00:07:33.460 align:middle line:90%
had visited me spontaneously.

00:07:33.460 --> 00:07:34.315 align:middle line:90%


00:07:34.315 --> 00:07:36.565 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And at that point,
did you begin your travels?

00:07:36.565 --> 00:07:37.657 align:middle line:90%


00:07:37.657 --> 00:07:38.490 align:middle line:90%
Where did you start?

00:07:38.490 --> 00:07:40.656 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, I was living
in New York at the time.

00:07:40.656 --> 00:07:41.550 align:middle line:90%


00:07:41.550 --> 00:07:46.560 align:middle line:84%
And so I did all the
things that seekers do.

00:07:46.560 --> 00:07:47.650 align:middle line:90%
I learned how to meditate.

00:07:47.650 --> 00:07:51.460 align:middle line:84%
I started getting up
very early and reading

00:07:51.460 --> 00:07:55.432 align:middle line:84%
books about meditation
and yoga and philosophy.

00:07:55.432 --> 00:07:56.640 align:middle line:90%
I wanted to learn everything.

00:07:56.640 --> 00:07:58.980 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to see every possible
different kind of teacher

00:07:58.980 --> 00:08:00.605 align:middle line:84%
from every different
kind of tradition.

00:08:00.605 --> 00:08:02.120 align:middle line:90%
I was voraciously curious.

00:08:02.120 --> 00:08:04.930 align:middle line:84%
And I've always been a
very skeptical person,

00:08:04.930 --> 00:08:08.200 align:middle line:84%
curious and skeptical, but
also very sincere and earnest.

00:08:08.200 --> 00:08:12.140 align:middle line:90%
And I had many teachers.

00:08:12.140 --> 00:08:15.240 align:middle line:84%
I went through all kinds
of different experiences

00:08:15.240 --> 00:08:17.490 align:middle line:84%
with meditation with
different people,

00:08:17.490 --> 00:08:19.490 align:middle line:84%
with different individuals
and different groups.

00:08:19.490 --> 00:08:21.906 align:middle line:84%
And I was learning and learning
and learning and learning.

00:08:21.906 --> 00:08:27.301 align:middle line:84%
And because I was a baby boomer,
when we became interested

00:08:27.301 --> 00:08:29.300 align:middle line:84%
in spirit, we didn't look
to our own traditions.

00:08:29.300 --> 00:08:31.846 align:middle line:84%
Because I'm Jewish, I didn't
look to my own tradition.

00:08:31.846 --> 00:08:33.100 align:middle line:90%
I looked to the East.

00:08:33.100 --> 00:08:35.929 align:middle line:90%


00:08:35.929 --> 00:08:40.030 align:middle line:84%
And at that time, all the
most famous luminaries,

00:08:40.030 --> 00:08:42.429 align:middle line:84%
the greatest Indian spiritual
teachers and masters,

00:08:42.429 --> 00:08:44.250 align:middle line:90%
were all coming to the West.

00:08:44.250 --> 00:08:46.490 align:middle line:84%
And I'd also met
many people that

00:08:46.490 --> 00:08:48.676 align:middle line:84%
had spent long periods
of time in India.

00:08:48.676 --> 00:08:50.050 align:middle line:84%
And when I met
them, I could tell

00:08:50.050 --> 00:08:51.790 align:middle line:84%
that they weren't necessarily
that much more enlightened

00:08:51.790 --> 00:08:53.310 align:middle line:84%
than I was, which
meant that I knew

00:08:53.310 --> 00:08:55.330 align:middle line:84%
that going to India,
itself, wasn't the answer.

00:08:55.330 --> 00:08:55.830 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Ah.

00:08:55.830 --> 00:08:56.680 align:middle line:90%


00:08:56.680 --> 00:08:58.780 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: But I felt very
compelled to go anyway.

00:08:58.780 --> 00:09:00.195 align:middle line:84%
At a certain point
when I was 27,

00:09:00.195 --> 00:09:01.820 align:middle line:84%
I felt I wanted to
go for a few months.

00:09:01.820 --> 00:09:03.160 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Part of your journey.

00:09:03.160 --> 00:09:04.420 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, I
was just curious,

00:09:04.420 --> 00:09:06.503 align:middle line:84%
even though I had already
had a lot of experiences

00:09:06.503 --> 00:09:08.530 align:middle line:84%
and met many teachers
and that kind of thing.

00:09:08.530 --> 00:09:13.460 align:middle line:84%
And when I arrived
there, I suddenly

00:09:13.460 --> 00:09:15.230 align:middle line:84%
felt an enormous
feeling of happiness.

00:09:15.230 --> 00:09:18.389 align:middle line:84%
And the reason was is because
I was a very dedicated seeker.

00:09:18.389 --> 00:09:20.430 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I wanted to become
an enlightened person.

00:09:20.430 --> 00:09:21.950 align:middle line:84%
That was more important
to me than anything else.

00:09:21.950 --> 00:09:24.660 align:middle line:84%
And of course, if you live in
New York City, everybody looks

00:09:24.660 --> 00:09:25.470 align:middle line:90%
at, what do you do?

00:09:25.470 --> 00:09:26.500 align:middle line:90%
Everyone says, what do you do?

00:09:26.500 --> 00:09:27.375 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right, right.

00:09:27.375 --> 00:09:28.140 align:middle line:90%


00:09:28.140 --> 00:09:30.450 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: And I didn't really
have a very good response.

00:09:30.450 --> 00:09:32.325 align:middle line:84%
I would tell people what
I was interested in,

00:09:32.325 --> 00:09:34.260 align:middle line:84%
and most people looked--
they were polite.

00:09:34.260 --> 00:09:35.310 align:middle line:84%
But I could tell
they couldn't relate

00:09:35.310 --> 00:09:36.810 align:middle line:84%
to what I was
interested in, and they

00:09:36.810 --> 00:09:37.840 align:middle line:90%
thought I was little crazy.

00:09:37.840 --> 00:09:38.520 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You would
tell them that you

00:09:38.520 --> 00:09:40.186 align:middle line:84%
were interested in
becoming enlightened?

00:09:40.186 --> 00:09:40.962 align:middle line:90%


00:09:40.962 --> 00:09:42.920 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: I can't remember
exactly what I said--

00:09:42.920 --> 00:09:44.680 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yeah, I mean, but that's
basically what you were-- yeah.

00:09:44.680 --> 00:09:46.040 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Something in that--
I mean, I wasn't naive.

00:09:46.040 --> 00:09:47.581 align:middle line:84%
I probably would
have put it in words

00:09:47.581 --> 00:09:49.210 align:middle line:84%
that would have
been at least they

00:09:49.210 --> 00:09:50.180 align:middle line:90%
would have been receptive to.

00:09:50.180 --> 00:09:52.305 align:middle line:84%
But it wasn't anything most
people could relate to.

00:09:52.305 --> 00:09:54.660 align:middle line:84%
So when I arrived
in India, I just

00:09:54.660 --> 00:09:56.680 align:middle line:84%
felt this freedom
that I could really

00:09:56.680 --> 00:10:00.135 align:middle line:84%
pursue this passion I had
without any inhibitions.

00:10:00.135 --> 00:10:02.010 align:middle line:84%
Because India is a place
where people can get

00:10:02.010 --> 00:10:04.162 align:middle line:90%
lost, and they can also escape.

00:10:04.162 --> 00:10:06.120 align:middle line:84%
And it's a place where
people can truly awaken.

00:10:06.120 --> 00:10:09.009 align:middle line:84%
So I had a small
income at the time.

00:10:09.009 --> 00:10:11.133 align:middle line:84%
It wasn't much, but it was
enough to live in India.

00:10:11.133 --> 00:10:12.799 align:middle line:84%
And I decided I wasn't
going to go back.

00:10:12.799 --> 00:10:13.860 align:middle line:90%


00:10:13.860 --> 00:10:14.800 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: So you stayed.

00:10:14.800 --> 00:10:15.710 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: So I stayed.

00:10:15.710 --> 00:10:17.850 align:middle line:84%
And I stayed for
2 and 1/2 years.

00:10:17.850 --> 00:10:20.871 align:middle line:90%


00:10:20.871 --> 00:10:22.370 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Did you
find a teacher there

00:10:22.370 --> 00:10:24.832 align:middle line:84%
that you resonated
with and learned from?

00:10:24.832 --> 00:10:26.290 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well,
right before I left,

00:10:26.290 --> 00:10:28.920 align:middle line:84%
I heard of a teacher who
eventually became very famous,

00:10:28.920 --> 00:10:30.670 align:middle line:84%
but at that time he
was very little known.

00:10:30.670 --> 00:10:35.060 align:middle line:84%
His name was H.W.L Poonja
or Poonjaji, or as Papaji

00:10:35.060 --> 00:10:36.640 align:middle line:90%
as he's become known.

00:10:36.640 --> 00:10:38.220 align:middle line:90%


00:10:38.220 --> 00:10:41.730 align:middle line:84%
And he was a disciple of the
great 20th-century renowned

00:10:41.730 --> 00:10:43.980 align:middle line:84%
spiritual master
Ramana Maharshi.

00:10:43.980 --> 00:10:45.610 align:middle line:90%
He was a direct disciple of his.

00:10:45.610 --> 00:10:50.460 align:middle line:84%
And I'd had never met a
master of Advaita Vedanta

00:10:50.460 --> 00:10:53.460 align:middle line:84%
or a disciple of the
great Ramana Maharshi.

00:10:53.460 --> 00:10:55.620 align:middle line:84%
And I'd heard a lot
about him from a friend,

00:10:55.620 --> 00:10:58.290 align:middle line:84%
and so I was very curious and
interested to go visit him.

00:10:58.290 --> 00:11:00.185 align:middle line:84%
I was actually on
my way to Korea.

00:11:00.185 --> 00:11:03.090 align:middle line:84%
I was going to go
live a life of a monk.

00:11:03.090 --> 00:11:05.080 align:middle line:84%
I was going to go live--
I knew at that point

00:11:05.080 --> 00:11:06.470 align:middle line:84%
that this thing was
going to happen to me.

00:11:06.470 --> 00:11:07.390 align:middle line:90%
I was very convinced.

00:11:07.390 --> 00:11:09.400 align:middle line:84%
I had a lot of
confidence about it.

00:11:09.400 --> 00:11:12.150 align:middle line:84%
I just felt I needed
to be in a place

00:11:12.150 --> 00:11:15.047 align:middle line:84%
where I'd be able to live
a very disciplined life.

00:11:15.047 --> 00:11:17.630 align:middle line:84%
And I was sure, sooner or later,
it was just a matter of time.

00:11:17.630 --> 00:11:20.199 align:middle line:84%
So I was more or less
on my way to leave India

00:11:20.199 --> 00:11:21.240 align:middle line:90%
when I went to visit him.

00:11:21.240 --> 00:11:22.320 align:middle line:90%


00:11:22.320 --> 00:11:25.560 align:middle line:84%
And as I said, at the
time he was quite unknown.

00:11:25.560 --> 00:11:28.250 align:middle line:90%
He was an old man.

00:11:28.250 --> 00:11:30.830 align:middle line:84%
He was living in his
son's house in Lucknow.

00:11:30.830 --> 00:11:33.290 align:middle line:84%
And when I went into
the room to see him,

00:11:33.290 --> 00:11:35.710 align:middle line:84%
he was sitting on his
bed in an undershirt.

00:11:35.710 --> 00:11:37.815 align:middle line:84%
He was a family-- he'd
been a householder.

00:11:37.815 --> 00:11:41.054 align:middle line:84%
So he didn't have religious
attire on or robes

00:11:41.054 --> 00:11:41.970 align:middle line:90%
or anything like that.

00:11:41.970 --> 00:11:43.511 align:middle line:84%
He was just sitting
in his undershirt

00:11:43.511 --> 00:11:45.260 align:middle line:90%
and alone on his bed.

00:11:45.260 --> 00:11:46.995 align:middle line:84%
And I'd been a seeker
for a long time.

00:11:46.995 --> 00:11:48.120 align:middle line:90%
I'd seen a lot of teachers.

00:11:48.120 --> 00:11:50.590 align:middle line:84%
And I wanted to let him know
that I didn't expect much

00:11:50.590 --> 00:11:51.090 align:middle line:90%
from him.

00:11:51.090 --> 00:11:52.360 align:middle line:84%
And I said, I have
no expectations.

00:11:52.360 --> 00:11:53.651 align:middle line:90%
And he said, well, that's good.

00:11:53.651 --> 00:11:54.870 align:middle line:90%


00:11:54.870 --> 00:11:59.220 align:middle line:84%
And he obviously had
a tremendous amount

00:11:59.220 --> 00:12:03.800 align:middle line:84%
of confidence, a deep,
otherworldly confidence.

00:12:03.800 --> 00:12:06.830 align:middle line:84%
And so I sat on the floor
in front of his bed.

00:12:06.830 --> 00:12:09.020 align:middle line:84%
And I was with a
friend, and we started

00:12:09.020 --> 00:12:10.180 align:middle line:90%
asking him some questions.

00:12:10.180 --> 00:12:13.820 align:middle line:84%
And the question was, how much
effort does it take to be free?

00:12:13.820 --> 00:12:15.920 align:middle line:90%


00:12:15.920 --> 00:12:19.060 align:middle line:84%
And he whispered, he
whispered, he said,

00:12:19.060 --> 00:12:21.870 align:middle line:84%
you don't have to make
any effort to be free.

00:12:21.870 --> 00:12:24.120 align:middle line:84%
And when he whispered
those few words,

00:12:24.120 --> 00:12:28.890 align:middle line:84%
something happened inside
my being, my consciousness.

00:12:28.890 --> 00:12:31.520 align:middle line:84%
I suddenly became aware
of a brook of water

00:12:31.520 --> 00:12:33.400 align:middle line:90%
running down the side of a hill.

00:12:33.400 --> 00:12:37.880 align:middle line:84%
I realized that my true nature
was like that water, which

00:12:37.880 --> 00:12:40.710 align:middle line:84%
was that, like water, nothing
can obstruct the flow of water.

00:12:40.710 --> 00:12:42.050 align:middle line:90%
It was always free.

00:12:42.050 --> 00:12:45.190 align:middle line:84%
And I realized in that moment
that I had never been unfree,

00:12:45.190 --> 00:12:47.760 align:middle line:84%
that the illusion had
been-- that bondage

00:12:47.760 --> 00:12:50.610 align:middle line:84%
was an illusion, that there was
a block or something in my way

00:12:50.610 --> 00:12:51.540 align:middle line:90%
had been the illusion.

00:12:51.540 --> 00:12:54.500 align:middle line:84%
What was real, was true, and
what had always been true

00:12:54.500 --> 00:12:55.950 align:middle line:90%
is that I'd always been free.

00:12:55.950 --> 00:12:58.250 align:middle line:84%
I just had never
known it before.

00:12:58.250 --> 00:12:59.910 align:middle line:84%
And I was just
looking at the ground.

00:12:59.910 --> 00:13:01.410 align:middle line:84%
This probably took
about 10 seconds.

00:13:01.410 --> 00:13:04.555 align:middle line:84%
I was looking at the ground,
and he said, that's it!

00:13:04.555 --> 00:13:05.310 align:middle line:90%
And he burst out.

00:13:05.310 --> 00:13:07.440 align:middle line:84%
And I looked up and I
said, how did you know?

00:13:07.440 --> 00:13:10.230 align:middle line:84%
Because this was just 10 seconds
or 20 seconds of silence.

00:13:10.230 --> 00:13:11.940 align:middle line:90%
And he burst out laughing.

00:13:11.940 --> 00:13:12.690 align:middle line:90%
And that was the--

00:13:12.690 --> 00:13:15.100 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: He saw
that shift in you.

00:13:15.100 --> 00:13:16.210 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: Yeah.

00:13:16.210 --> 00:13:18.640 align:middle line:84%
Then I said, well,
who is this man?

00:13:18.640 --> 00:13:22.110 align:middle line:84%
So then I spent three
weeks in Lucknow,

00:13:22.110 --> 00:13:24.770 align:middle line:84%
and I stayed in some
small hotel by myself.

00:13:24.770 --> 00:13:26.662 align:middle line:84%
And I would go visit
him in the mornings,

00:13:26.662 --> 00:13:27.940 align:middle line:90%
and we'd go for walks.

00:13:27.940 --> 00:13:30.910 align:middle line:84%
And then I would go to
his-- I would usually

00:13:30.910 --> 00:13:34.030 align:middle line:84%
have lunch with his family
and his son's family.

00:13:34.030 --> 00:13:35.092 align:middle line:90%
Then I would go.

00:13:35.092 --> 00:13:37.050 align:middle line:84%
Come back in the afternoons
after he had a nap,

00:13:37.050 --> 00:13:40.480 align:middle line:84%
and we'd spend time
going for walks,

00:13:40.480 --> 00:13:42.430 align:middle line:84%
having talks, just
sitting quietly together.

00:13:42.430 --> 00:13:43.700 align:middle line:90%


00:13:43.700 --> 00:13:48.870 align:middle line:84%
And he answered a couple
of fundamental questions

00:13:48.870 --> 00:13:49.930 align:middle line:90%
that I had.

00:13:49.930 --> 00:13:54.020 align:middle line:84%
And one was I wanted to know-- I
had had this initial experience

00:13:54.020 --> 00:13:56.890 align:middle line:84%
when I was a young
teenager of the fullness,

00:13:56.890 --> 00:14:00.680 align:middle line:84%
of the effulgence of the
splendor of the absolute.

00:14:00.680 --> 00:14:02.180 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Did he
uncover that for you?

00:14:02.180 --> 00:14:02.860 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: Well, right.

00:14:02.860 --> 00:14:04.910 align:middle line:84%
But then I had been
spending time with Buddhists

00:14:04.910 --> 00:14:06.743 align:middle line:84%
and doing all kinds of
Buddhist meditations.

00:14:06.743 --> 00:14:08.720 align:middle line:84%
And Buddha said
that "emptiness is

00:14:08.720 --> 00:14:10.930 align:middle line:90%
the ultimate nature of reality."

00:14:10.930 --> 00:14:11.990 align:middle line:90%
And I was very confused.

00:14:11.990 --> 00:14:13.770 align:middle line:84%
I said, well, what is the
ultimate nature of reality?

00:14:13.770 --> 00:14:15.895 align:middle line:84%
It was a very profound
existential question for me.

00:14:15.895 --> 00:14:17.730 align:middle line:84%
And I asked him, what's
the ultimate truth?

00:14:17.730 --> 00:14:19.179 align:middle line:90%
Is it fullness or emptiness?

00:14:19.179 --> 00:14:20.220 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Was it emptiness?

00:14:20.220 --> 00:14:21.803 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: And he said,
they're both two

00:14:21.803 --> 00:14:23.480 align:middle line:90%
sides of the same coin.

00:14:23.480 --> 00:14:23.980 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Ah.

00:14:23.980 --> 00:14:24.760 align:middle line:90%
So it's--

00:14:24.760 --> 00:14:27.060 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: So they are one.

00:14:27.060 --> 00:14:28.690 align:middle line:84%
And from one
perspective, there's

00:14:28.690 --> 00:14:30.940 align:middle line:84%
emptiness, and the other
perspective they're fullness.

00:14:30.940 --> 00:14:32.650 align:middle line:84%
But they're not
two, they're one.

00:14:32.650 --> 00:14:34.420 align:middle line:84%
So this relieved a
tremendous amount

00:14:34.420 --> 00:14:36.480 align:middle line:84%
of existential doubt
and struggle I had.

00:14:36.480 --> 00:14:38.790 align:middle line:84%
And the last thing
that happened,

00:14:38.790 --> 00:14:40.880 align:middle line:84%
as I told him about this
extraordinary thing that

00:14:40.880 --> 00:14:43.450 align:middle line:84%
happened when I was 16,
this amazing visitation

00:14:43.450 --> 00:14:45.729 align:middle line:84%
from the unknown, and I
told him in a lot of detail,

00:14:45.729 --> 00:14:48.270 align:middle line:84%
and he looked at me and he said,
you already know everything.

00:14:48.270 --> 00:14:49.650 align:middle line:90%


00:14:49.650 --> 00:14:53.296 align:middle line:84%
And because of his tremendous
spiritual authority,

00:14:53.296 --> 00:14:55.420 align:middle line:84%
the minute he said that,
I could feel something let

00:14:55.420 --> 00:14:58.740 align:middle line:90%
go in the core of my being.

00:14:58.740 --> 00:15:01.270 align:middle line:84%
And this kind of
catapulted me into kind

00:15:01.270 --> 00:15:03.150 align:middle line:84%
of an altered state
of consciousness

00:15:03.150 --> 00:15:09.510 align:middle line:84%
and catalyzed a process that
happened after I left him.

00:15:09.510 --> 00:15:12.630 align:middle line:84%
But this, it was
almost like that I

00:15:12.630 --> 00:15:15.760 align:middle line:84%
was able to accept at a very
deep level something that

00:15:15.760 --> 00:15:18.600 align:middle line:84%
had been revealed to me when
I was a very young person.

00:15:18.600 --> 00:15:21.170 align:middle line:84%
And then, finally, after
three weeks, I was gonna--

00:15:21.170 --> 00:15:23.420 align:middle line:84%
I left him for a few
weeks to go visit friends.

00:15:23.420 --> 00:15:26.770 align:middle line:84%
And he'd tell me, something very
big is going to happen to you.

00:15:26.770 --> 00:15:29.010 align:middle line:90%
And I said, really?

00:15:29.010 --> 00:15:32.110 align:middle line:84%
He said, yeah, something very
big is going to happen to you.

00:15:32.110 --> 00:15:35.690 align:middle line:84%
When I was with him, as often
happens in these circumstances,

00:15:35.690 --> 00:15:37.390 align:middle line:84%
I would go from
thinking that I'm

00:15:37.390 --> 00:15:40.190 align:middle line:84%
with some extraordinary
spiritual giant,

00:15:40.190 --> 00:15:42.630 align:middle line:84%
some spiritual master that
the world does not know about,

00:15:42.630 --> 00:15:44.532 align:middle line:84%
to I'm with just some
crazy old man that

00:15:44.532 --> 00:15:45.500 align:middle line:84%
doesn't know what
he's talking about.

00:15:45.500 --> 00:15:46.767 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I'm sure that went--

00:15:46.767 --> 00:15:49.100 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: So when he told me
that something big was going

00:15:49.100 --> 00:15:51.660 align:middle line:84%
to happen, I didn't know
what he was talking about.

00:15:51.660 --> 00:15:53.660 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know how he could
possibly know anyway.

00:15:53.660 --> 00:15:54.680 align:middle line:90%


00:15:54.680 --> 00:15:59.720 align:middle line:84%
But then when I left him, I left
him and took the train to New

00:15:59.720 --> 00:16:06.150 align:middle line:84%
Delhi, something happened,
some energetic current

00:16:06.150 --> 00:16:09.080 align:middle line:84%
had started to flow
inside my being.

00:16:09.080 --> 00:16:11.060 align:middle line:84%
But it wasn't really
in my physical body,

00:16:11.060 --> 00:16:12.956 align:middle line:90%
but it's something that I felt.

00:16:12.956 --> 00:16:19.090 align:middle line:84%
It was a current of bliss,
an intensity of energy

00:16:19.090 --> 00:16:21.210 align:middle line:90%
that would wax and wane.

00:16:21.210 --> 00:16:25.880 align:middle line:84%
It would get very intense, and
it would get to be too much,

00:16:25.880 --> 00:16:27.660 align:middle line:90%
and it would fall back again.

00:16:27.660 --> 00:16:30.220 align:middle line:84%
And this lasted for
about three weeks.

00:16:30.220 --> 00:16:33.350 align:middle line:84%
And I felt like I
was being consumed

00:16:33.350 --> 00:16:36.600 align:middle line:84%
by a presence, an energetic
presence that I couldn't see.

00:16:36.600 --> 00:16:38.244 align:middle line:84%
And it was the most
incredible-- it

00:16:38.244 --> 00:16:39.910 align:middle line:84%
was the most incredible
time in my life.

00:16:39.910 --> 00:16:43.230 align:middle line:84%
And when I went to
Delhi, I met a friend,

00:16:43.230 --> 00:16:45.980 align:middle line:84%
and I started telling them
what had happ-- you know,

00:16:45.980 --> 00:16:48.350 align:middle line:84%
my time with this
extraordinary man.

00:16:48.350 --> 00:16:51.070 align:middle line:84%
And as I told them
the story, they

00:16:51.070 --> 00:16:53.330 align:middle line:84%
were catapulted into the
same state of consciousness

00:16:53.330 --> 00:16:53.930 align:middle line:90%
that I was in.

00:16:53.930 --> 00:16:55.720 align:middle line:84%
And then I didn't know
what was happening.

00:16:55.720 --> 00:16:59.200 align:middle line:84%
Because what was my-- what felt
like my own purely subjective

00:16:59.200 --> 00:17:02.510 align:middle line:84%
experience began to be this
inter-subjective or shared

00:17:02.510 --> 00:17:04.180 align:middle line:90%
experience with another person.

00:17:04.180 --> 00:17:06.000 align:middle line:84%
And this started
happening with all people

00:17:06.000 --> 00:17:07.972 align:middle line:84%
that I was sharing
my process with.

00:17:07.972 --> 00:17:09.930 align:middle line:84%
They actually started to
experience it directly

00:17:09.930 --> 00:17:10.429 align:middle line:90%
themselves.

00:17:10.429 --> 00:17:11.230 align:middle line:90%


00:17:11.230 --> 00:17:13.016 align:middle line:84%
When this happened,
this really--

00:17:13.016 --> 00:17:14.599 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Blew your
mind, I'm sure, yes.

00:17:14.599 --> 00:17:16.307 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Blew my mind
in the biggest way.

00:17:16.307 --> 00:17:18.540 align:middle line:84%
And so that continued
for these three weeks.

00:17:18.540 --> 00:17:19.700 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So it was an
energetic transmission

00:17:19.700 --> 00:17:20.630 align:middle line:90%
almost of experience.

00:17:20.630 --> 00:17:22.569 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Very,
extremely powerfully.

00:17:22.569 --> 00:17:25.730 align:middle line:84%
And then after three weeks,
I went back to see him.

00:17:25.730 --> 00:17:30.270 align:middle line:84%
And all my doubts about him had
left, and I fell at his feet.

00:17:30.270 --> 00:17:31.420 align:middle line:90%


00:17:31.420 --> 00:17:32.570 align:middle line:90%
And he burst out laughing.

00:17:32.570 --> 00:17:33.747 align:middle line:90%


00:17:33.747 --> 00:17:34.580 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting.

00:17:34.580 --> 00:17:35.345 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: And so
this was a real--

00:17:35.345 --> 00:17:36.489 align:middle line:90%
it was a fairy tale story.

00:17:36.489 --> 00:17:38.280 align:middle line:84%
He thought at the time
he was going to die.

00:17:38.280 --> 00:17:39.380 align:middle line:90%
He was quite ill.

00:17:39.380 --> 00:17:42.190 align:middle line:84%
So he told me, "I want you
to accept responsibility

00:17:42.190 --> 00:17:44.240 align:middle line:90%
for the work," quote unquote.

00:17:44.240 --> 00:17:46.410 align:middle line:90%
I give you my robe and ball.

00:17:46.410 --> 00:17:48.900 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't really know what
to make of all these things.

00:17:48.900 --> 00:17:50.110 align:middle line:90%


00:17:50.110 --> 00:17:52.740 align:middle line:84%
I was flipping
into another world

00:17:52.740 --> 00:17:55.080 align:middle line:84%
that I felt I had no
background or training for.

00:17:55.080 --> 00:17:57.930 align:middle line:84%
And then I left him, and I went
with a small group of friends

00:17:57.930 --> 00:17:59.320 align:middle line:90%
to Rishikesh in northern India.

00:17:59.320 --> 00:18:01.569 align:middle line:84%
That's where the Beatles
went to be with the Maharishi

00:18:01.569 --> 00:18:02.259 align:middle line:90%
on the Ganges.

00:18:02.259 --> 00:18:03.550 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Very famous area, yeah.

00:18:03.550 --> 00:18:07.690 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: We stayed there for,
it was for about six weeks.

00:18:07.690 --> 00:18:10.570 align:middle line:84%
And then I became a
spiritual teacher overnight.

00:18:10.570 --> 00:18:13.555 align:middle line:84%
I was teaching all
day and every night.

00:18:13.555 --> 00:18:15.902 align:middle line:84%
We'd all sit in my room
together, and we would spend--

00:18:15.902 --> 00:18:18.110 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And the teachings
that you had learned from--

00:18:18.110 --> 00:18:18.860 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: Well, no.

00:18:18.860 --> 00:18:20.640 align:middle line:84%
What happened was it
was very spontaneous.

00:18:20.640 --> 00:18:24.140 align:middle line:84%
I suddenly had access to a
level of wisdom and depth

00:18:24.140 --> 00:18:28.846 align:middle line:84%
and knowledge that I felt
I hadn't been trained for.

00:18:28.846 --> 00:18:29.762 align:middle line:90%
It suddenly was there.

00:18:29.762 --> 00:18:31.680 align:middle line:90%
It was like going from 0 to 60.

00:18:31.680 --> 00:18:34.300 align:middle line:84%
And so then it was
really a process

00:18:34.300 --> 00:18:37.240 align:middle line:84%
of surrendering to a process
that was happening to me.

00:18:37.240 --> 00:18:40.065 align:middle line:84%
And I also had to be willing
to trust him unconditionally

00:18:40.065 --> 00:18:42.570 align:middle line:84%
because he told me this
was going to be my destiny

00:18:42.570 --> 00:18:44.490 align:middle line:84%
and this is what
I was going to do.

00:18:44.490 --> 00:18:46.040 align:middle line:84%
And so I didn't
believe I was ready.

00:18:46.040 --> 00:18:47.748 align:middle line:84%
I didn't believe I
could do such a thing.

00:18:47.748 --> 00:18:49.660 align:middle line:90%
But I needed to trust him.

00:18:49.660 --> 00:18:52.185 align:middle line:84%
And in doing that, it
was happening by itself.

00:18:52.185 --> 00:18:53.560 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So do
these concepts have

00:18:53.560 --> 00:18:55.650 align:middle line:84%
to do with what you
teach around non-duality?

00:18:55.650 --> 00:18:58.160 align:middle line:90%


00:18:58.160 --> 00:19:00.410 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, whenever we
use the word enlightenment,

00:19:00.410 --> 00:19:04.200 align:middle line:84%
we're always pointing to an
experience of non-duality.

00:19:04.200 --> 00:19:05.700 align:middle line:84%
But what's interesting
to understand

00:19:05.700 --> 00:19:09.090 align:middle line:84%
is that the meaning of that
word has evolved and shifted

00:19:09.090 --> 00:19:13.330 align:middle line:84%
over time, especially in
relationship to Eastern

00:19:13.330 --> 00:19:15.550 align:middle line:84%
spirituality and to
the Eastern traditions.

00:19:15.550 --> 00:19:16.550 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Non-dualism has?

00:19:16.550 --> 00:19:16.890 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: Yes.

00:19:16.890 --> 00:19:17.598 align:middle line:90%
Well, absolutely.

00:19:17.598 --> 00:19:20.250 align:middle line:84%
So for example, in the
original Buddhist teaching,

00:19:20.250 --> 00:19:23.660 align:middle line:84%
the original Buddhist
teaching, his enlightenment

00:19:23.660 --> 00:19:26.060 align:middle line:84%
was about the experience
of transcending the world

00:19:26.060 --> 00:19:30.670 align:middle line:84%
completely, about entering into
a very deep, meditative state.

00:19:30.670 --> 00:19:31.800 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:19:31.800 --> 00:19:34.160 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: And when
we meditate, when

00:19:34.160 --> 00:19:35.850 align:middle line:84%
we enter into a
meditative state,

00:19:35.850 --> 00:19:38.200 align:middle line:84%
we make the effort to
transcend the mind,

00:19:38.200 --> 00:19:40.234 align:middle line:84%
to go beyond the
thinking process.

00:19:40.234 --> 00:19:42.650 align:middle line:84%
And when you go beyond the
mind and go beyond the thinking

00:19:42.650 --> 00:19:48.320 align:middle line:84%
process, as the conditioned
movement of thought

00:19:48.320 --> 00:19:50.635 align:middle line:84%
moves into the background,
interestingly enough,

00:19:50.635 --> 00:19:53.010 align:middle line:84%
simultaneously our awareness
of the passing of time moves

00:19:53.010 --> 00:19:54.380 align:middle line:90%
into the background.

00:19:54.380 --> 00:19:57.480 align:middle line:84%
And when thought and mind
move into the background,

00:19:57.480 --> 00:19:59.090 align:middle line:90%
time moves into the background.

00:19:59.090 --> 00:20:02.060 align:middle line:84%
So when thought and mind and
time move into the background,

00:20:02.060 --> 00:20:03.759 align:middle line:84%
our awareness of
the external world

00:20:03.759 --> 00:20:05.050 align:middle line:90%
also moves into the background.

00:20:05.050 --> 00:20:06.300 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I can understand that.

00:20:06.300 --> 00:20:07.770 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: And so
if we keep letting

00:20:07.770 --> 00:20:09.890 align:middle line:84%
go and keep letting
go, what will happen

00:20:09.890 --> 00:20:11.815 align:middle line:84%
is when-- thought
eventually will disappear.

00:20:11.815 --> 00:20:13.050 align:middle line:90%


00:20:13.050 --> 00:20:15.820 align:middle line:84%
When thought disappears,
time disappears.

00:20:15.820 --> 00:20:17.945 align:middle line:84%
When time disappears, our
awareness of the world

00:20:17.945 --> 00:20:18.445 align:middle line:90%
disappears.

00:20:18.445 --> 00:20:19.570 align:middle line:90%


00:20:19.570 --> 00:20:22.940 align:middle line:84%
When our awareness of the world
disappears, if we keep letting

00:20:22.940 --> 00:20:24.790 align:middle line:84%
go and keep letting
go, eventually even

00:20:24.790 --> 00:20:27.010 align:middle line:84%
our sense of and awareness
of our own physical form

00:20:27.010 --> 00:20:28.047 align:middle line:90%
disappears.

00:20:28.047 --> 00:20:29.755 align:middle line:84%
So when mind disappears,
time disappears.

00:20:29.755 --> 00:20:31.730 align:middle line:84%
When time disappears,
world disappears.

00:20:31.730 --> 00:20:34.735 align:middle line:84%
When world disappears,
ultimately form disappears.

00:20:34.735 --> 00:20:38.637 align:middle line:84%
So when everything disappears,
we make the greatest discovery

00:20:38.637 --> 00:20:40.220 align:middle line:84%
that all the greatest
mystics from all

00:20:40.220 --> 00:20:43.260 align:middle line:84%
the great mystical
traditions had,

00:20:43.260 --> 00:20:45.705 align:middle line:84%
which is when everything
disappears, I'm still here.

00:20:45.705 --> 00:20:46.580 align:middle line:90%
I didn't go anywhere.

00:20:46.580 --> 00:20:47.490 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right, right.

00:20:47.490 --> 00:20:50.734 align:middle line:84%
That's not very
practical if I disappear.

00:20:50.734 --> 00:20:51.400 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: No, no.

00:20:51.400 --> 00:20:53.400 align:middle line:84%
But we realize, because we
usually think, I'm the body,

00:20:53.400 --> 00:20:55.010 align:middle line:84%
I'm the mind, I'm
the personality.

00:20:55.010 --> 00:20:57.051 align:middle line:84%
And you realize when all
of that has disappeared,

00:20:57.051 --> 00:21:00.300 align:middle line:84%
when there's not even--
and there's no memory left,

00:21:00.300 --> 00:21:03.570 align:middle line:84%
our most intimately felt
sense of self is here

00:21:03.570 --> 00:21:06.950 align:middle line:84%
and is experienced as
beginningless and emptiness--

00:21:06.950 --> 00:21:08.490 align:middle line:90%
beginningless and endless.

00:21:08.490 --> 00:21:10.740 align:middle line:84%
Who I am has no
beginning and no end.

00:21:10.740 --> 00:21:14.300 align:middle line:84%
This is-- and this
is merely-- this

00:21:14.300 --> 00:21:17.510 align:middle line:84%
is the human form, shape
and form of who I am.

00:21:17.510 --> 00:21:20.187 align:middle line:84%
So what the Buddha was
teaching was the awakening--

00:21:20.187 --> 00:21:22.020 align:middle line:84%
the original Buddhist
teaching was awakening

00:21:22.020 --> 00:21:25.430 align:middle line:84%
to this timelessness
and formlessness, which

00:21:25.430 --> 00:21:27.670 align:middle line:84%
has been called the
ground of being,

00:21:27.670 --> 00:21:30.390 align:middle line:90%
timeless, formless being.

00:21:30.390 --> 00:21:33.470 align:middle line:84%
And so in the
original teaching, he

00:21:33.470 --> 00:21:35.060 align:middle line:84%
said that when you
awaken to being,

00:21:35.060 --> 00:21:39.380 align:middle line:84%
you awaken to the unborn, to
the deathless, to the uncreated,

00:21:39.380 --> 00:21:42.130 align:middle line:84%
to that which exists
before time and space.

00:21:42.130 --> 00:21:43.550 align:middle line:84%
You awaken to the
part of yourself

00:21:43.550 --> 00:21:44.550 align:middle line:90%
that has never been born.

00:21:44.550 --> 00:21:46.383 align:middle line:84%
So when you awaken to
that part of yourself,

00:21:46.383 --> 00:21:48.640 align:middle line:84%
you realize that the deepest
dimension of yourself

00:21:48.640 --> 00:21:51.490 align:middle line:84%
and the deepest dimension
of reality itself

00:21:51.490 --> 00:21:54.150 align:middle line:84%
is immortal and
uncreated and unborn.

00:21:54.150 --> 00:21:56.870 align:middle line:84%
And when you realize
that, it frees you

00:21:56.870 --> 00:22:00.260 align:middle line:84%
from attachment to this body, to
this mind, to this personality.

00:22:00.260 --> 00:22:02.990 align:middle line:84%
That was the Buddha's
original teaching.

00:22:02.990 --> 00:22:03.990 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And that's-- OK.

00:22:03.990 --> 00:22:05.740 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: But then
about 800 years later

00:22:05.740 --> 00:22:07.900 align:middle line:84%
in Buddhism with the
Mahayana revolution,

00:22:07.900 --> 00:22:12.250 align:middle line:84%
they realized that the nature of
the world, the nature of form,

00:22:12.250 --> 00:22:14.750 align:middle line:84%
is ultimately the same
as emptiness, all right.

00:22:14.750 --> 00:22:16.780 align:middle line:84%
The emptiness, this
timeless, formless

00:22:16.780 --> 00:22:18.870 align:middle line:84%
emptiness, this
ground of reality.

00:22:18.870 --> 00:22:22.880 align:middle line:84%
They realized that everything,
that the material world

00:22:22.880 --> 00:22:27.830 align:middle line:84%
is one with and not separate
with this primary foundation

00:22:27.830 --> 00:22:28.890 align:middle line:90%
of emptiness itself.

00:22:28.890 --> 00:22:31.060 align:middle line:84%
And that was when--
in the Heart Sutra

00:22:31.060 --> 00:22:33.450 align:middle line:84%
the Buddha says,
"Form is emptiness

00:22:33.450 --> 00:22:34.460 align:middle line:90%
and emptiness is form."

00:22:34.460 --> 00:22:36.530 align:middle line:84%
Form and emptiness
are one and not two.

00:22:36.530 --> 00:22:40.430 align:middle line:84%
And so in Mahayana-- in Mahayana
Buddhism, the world of form

00:22:40.430 --> 00:22:43.330 align:middle line:90%
is also embraced as emptiness.

00:22:43.330 --> 00:22:46.790 align:middle line:84%
In other words, the feeling
of I need to escape the world

00:22:46.790 --> 00:22:48.610 align:middle line:84%
or transcend the world
in order to become

00:22:48.610 --> 00:22:50.980 align:middle line:90%
enlightened is not true anymore.

00:22:50.980 --> 00:22:53.270 align:middle line:84%
Now I can embrace
the world of form

00:22:53.270 --> 00:22:57.264 align:middle line:84%
and use the experience of being
here in the world as a way

00:22:57.264 --> 00:22:58.180 align:middle line:90%
to become enlightened.

00:22:58.180 --> 00:22:59.980 align:middle line:84%
And there's been a third
turning of the wheel,

00:22:59.980 --> 00:23:01.420 align:middle line:84%
and that's what my
new book is all about.

00:23:01.420 --> 00:23:03.000 align:middle line:84%
And that's what the
new enlightenment

00:23:03.000 --> 00:23:06.450 align:middle line:84%
is all about, which is the
awakening to evolution.

00:23:06.450 --> 00:23:09.100 align:middle line:84%
Because we realize that it
was out of this primordial

00:23:09.100 --> 00:23:12.590 align:middle line:84%
emptiness, from this primordial
emptiness, this void,

00:23:12.590 --> 00:23:16.170 align:middle line:84%
that the Big Bang happened,
that the creative process

00:23:16.170 --> 00:23:17.760 align:middle line:84%
emerged from
primordial emptiness.

00:23:17.760 --> 00:23:21.300 align:middle line:84%
And this is when you
realize that everything

00:23:21.300 --> 00:23:24.130 align:middle line:84%
that exists in the world
of time and space-- matter

00:23:24.130 --> 00:23:29.165 align:middle line:84%
and energy, right, and sentient
life-- came from nothingness.

00:23:29.165 --> 00:23:30.590 align:middle line:90%


00:23:30.590 --> 00:23:32.690 align:middle line:84%
And we realize it's
actually going somewhere.

00:23:32.690 --> 00:23:35.410 align:middle line:84%
Evolutionary process means
we're on a creative journey.

00:23:35.410 --> 00:23:37.060 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: There's a video that
we have that shows this.

00:23:37.060 --> 00:23:37.550 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: Oh, good.

00:23:37.550 --> 00:23:38.091 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:23:38.091 --> 00:23:40.660 align:middle line:84%
That gives us an idea of
what this evolution is about.

00:23:40.660 --> 00:23:41.743 align:middle line:90%
Let's take a look at that.

