00:36:49.680 --> 00:36:51.676 align:middle line:84%
but it includes, but
transcends the world,

00:36:51.676 --> 00:36:53.195 align:middle line:84%
that's what the
authentic self is.

00:36:53.195 --> 00:36:58.420 align:middle line:90%


00:36:58.420 --> 00:37:00.030 align:middle line:84%
So usually this is
understood as kind

00:37:00.030 --> 00:37:02.120 align:middle line:90%
of-- it's called creativity.

00:37:02.120 --> 00:37:04.050 align:middle line:90%


00:37:04.050 --> 00:37:07.670 align:middle line:84%
But what I've done with this
notion of authentic self

00:37:07.670 --> 00:37:09.720 align:middle line:84%
is to say, well,
OK, now we're not

00:37:09.720 --> 00:37:11.870 align:middle line:84%
talking about making
music or making art.

00:37:11.870 --> 00:37:15.610 align:middle line:90%


00:37:15.610 --> 00:37:18.680 align:middle line:84%
We're talking about freeing
the self so the self

00:37:18.680 --> 00:37:22.238 align:middle line:84%
itself can become the instrument
that's playing that music.

00:37:22.238 --> 00:37:25.724 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:37:25.724 --> 00:37:39.200 align:middle line:90%


00:37:39.200 --> 00:37:40.810 align:middle line:90%
[END VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:37:40.810 --> 00:37:41.310 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:37:41.310 --> 00:37:44.310 align:middle line:84%
So how are these concepts
practical to us today?

00:37:44.310 --> 00:37:45.212 align:middle line:90%
How do you get here?

00:37:45.212 --> 00:37:46.420 align:middle line:90%
How do you get to this place?

00:37:46.420 --> 00:37:48.810 align:middle line:84%
What are some of the
teachings around that?

00:37:48.810 --> 00:37:51.100 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, I think--
I mean, the first thing

00:37:51.100 --> 00:37:59.370 align:middle line:84%
here is we have to be willing
to experience enormous-- allow

00:37:59.370 --> 00:38:05.460 align:middle line:84%
ourselves to experience enormous
frustration at the generally

00:38:05.460 --> 00:38:09.630 align:middle line:84%
superficial relationships
to existence that many of us

00:38:09.630 --> 00:38:11.670 align:middle line:84%
seem to tolerate without
it really bothering us.

00:38:11.670 --> 00:38:13.340 align:middle line:84%
We have to get to
a point, I believe,

00:38:13.340 --> 00:38:19.410 align:middle line:84%
where we get fed up with
living on the surface of life.

00:38:19.410 --> 00:38:21.990 align:middle line:84%
Because there's a certain
point, I think, when we get to--

00:38:21.990 --> 00:38:23.414 align:middle line:84%
and this happened
in my own life--

00:38:23.414 --> 00:38:24.830 align:middle line:84%
when I kind of
realized, you know,

00:38:24.830 --> 00:38:28.299 align:middle line:84%
if I didn't really wake
up, if I didn't achieve

00:38:28.299 --> 00:38:29.715 align:middle line:84%
some kind of
enormous breakthrough

00:38:29.715 --> 00:38:31.640 align:middle line:84%
and big transformation,
I was never

00:38:31.640 --> 00:38:33.170 align:middle line:90%
going to really be fully alive.

00:38:33.170 --> 00:38:34.510 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So what do you
mean by that frustration?

00:38:34.510 --> 00:38:35.580 align:middle line:90%
What does that look like?

00:38:35.580 --> 00:38:37.121 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well,
there's a frustration.

00:38:37.121 --> 00:38:41.150 align:middle line:84%
In other words, there's a
sense that, what am I doing?

00:38:41.150 --> 00:38:43.920 align:middle line:84%
Like what am I doing,
and why am I doing it?

00:38:43.920 --> 00:38:45.440 align:middle line:84%
And whose life am
I living anyway?

00:38:45.440 --> 00:38:46.212 align:middle line:90%


00:38:46.212 --> 00:38:48.170 align:middle line:84%
A lot of us aren't really
living our own lives.

00:38:48.170 --> 00:38:49.586 align:middle line:84%
I mean, to live
an authentic life,

00:38:49.586 --> 00:38:52.630 align:middle line:84%
we really have to-- we
have to dig very deep.

00:38:52.630 --> 00:38:56.560 align:middle line:84%
We have to be willing to
struggle with very big ideas,

00:38:56.560 --> 00:39:00.040 align:middle line:84%
challenge ourself, face
into the big questions,

00:39:00.040 --> 00:39:02.047 align:middle line:84%
peer way beyond the
boundaries of where

00:39:02.047 --> 00:39:03.380 align:middle line:90%
most people are willing to look.

00:39:03.380 --> 00:39:04.820 align:middle line:90%


00:39:04.820 --> 00:39:08.592 align:middle line:84%
And I think we have to
be willing to get fed up

00:39:08.592 --> 00:39:12.290 align:middle line:84%
with a life that's not
being lived with depth.

00:39:12.290 --> 00:39:17.920 align:middle line:84%
In other words, to live a
life of meaning and mastery

00:39:17.920 --> 00:39:20.790 align:middle line:84%
and what I call spiritual
self-confidence,

00:39:20.790 --> 00:39:24.110 align:middle line:84%
we have to be willing to make
the effort to break through

00:39:24.110 --> 00:39:28.960 align:middle line:84%
to the very center of what it
means to exist and to know that

00:39:28.960 --> 00:39:30.150 align:middle line:90%
for ourselves.

00:39:30.150 --> 00:39:33.220 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So the steps,
the how-to steps to this,

00:39:33.220 --> 00:39:37.090 align:middle line:84%
and the one, two, three to
that, or to breathing to relax

00:39:37.090 --> 00:39:39.310 align:middle line:84%
and so forth, is
really us just trying

00:39:39.310 --> 00:39:41.055 align:middle line:84%
to put a Band-Aid
on the frustration

00:39:41.055 --> 00:39:42.690 align:middle line:90%
that we're feeling with life?

00:39:42.690 --> 00:39:44.650 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, these
days, you know, it's here.

00:39:44.650 --> 00:39:46.360 align:middle line:84%
And it's also true
in India, by the way.

00:39:46.360 --> 00:39:47.910 align:middle line:84%
I spent a lot of
time there recently.

00:39:47.910 --> 00:39:49.290 align:middle line:90%


00:39:49.290 --> 00:39:50.840 align:middle line:84%
People experience
a lot of stress.

00:39:50.840 --> 00:39:52.720 align:middle line:90%
Life is very stressful.

00:39:52.720 --> 00:39:55.710 align:middle line:84%
The speed in which we're living
is getting quicker and quicker.

00:39:55.710 --> 00:39:57.290 align:middle line:84%
So it does create
a lot of stress.

00:39:57.290 --> 00:39:59.100 align:middle line:84%
It creates a lot of
insecurity, and it

00:39:59.100 --> 00:40:00.570 align:middle line:90%
creates a lot of anxiety.

00:40:00.570 --> 00:40:04.110 align:middle line:84%
So understandably, people
look to spiritual teachers

00:40:04.110 --> 00:40:06.560 align:middle line:84%
and spiritual
methodologies as a way

00:40:06.560 --> 00:40:10.565 align:middle line:84%
to calm down, to feel less
stressful and less frightened.

00:40:10.565 --> 00:40:12.560 align:middle line:84%
And if we learn how
to meditate, and we

00:40:12.560 --> 00:40:15.550 align:middle line:84%
learn some breathing exercises
and this kind of thing,

00:40:15.550 --> 00:40:17.406 align:middle line:84%
and learn how to
stretch our bodies out

00:40:17.406 --> 00:40:19.114 align:middle line:84%
and this kind of thing,
we can find a way

00:40:19.114 --> 00:40:22.520 align:middle line:84%
to experience a little bit
more equanimity or being

00:40:22.520 --> 00:40:24.360 align:middle line:90%
less anxious.

00:40:24.360 --> 00:40:26.600 align:middle line:84%
But there's a deeper
question, which

00:40:26.600 --> 00:40:29.190 align:middle line:90%
is you can calm yourself down.

00:40:29.190 --> 00:40:30.970 align:middle line:84%
We can calm down and
feel more peaceful.

00:40:30.970 --> 00:40:33.170 align:middle line:84%
But it doesn't necessarily
mean we've really

00:40:33.170 --> 00:40:35.160 align:middle line:84%
made any profound
breakthroughs that

00:40:35.160 --> 00:40:37.000 align:middle line:84%
have liberated us
on a soul level.

00:40:37.000 --> 00:40:39.040 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So it's more
of a temporary level.

00:40:39.040 --> 00:40:41.498 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: No, it's just a shift
in our emotional experience.

00:40:41.498 --> 00:40:43.500 align:middle line:84%
Instead of feeling
stressed out, we calm down.

00:40:43.500 --> 00:40:45.625 align:middle line:84%
You can have a couple of
drinks and calm down also.

00:40:45.625 --> 00:40:48.170 align:middle line:84%
But that doesn't
necessarily change or affect

00:40:48.170 --> 00:40:49.700 align:middle line:90%
the state of one's soul at all.

00:40:49.700 --> 00:40:52.530 align:middle line:84%
So what does is--
all the greatest

00:40:52.530 --> 00:40:55.130 align:middle line:84%
philosophers and the greatest
mystics throughout history

00:40:55.130 --> 00:40:57.070 align:middle line:84%
are individuals who
realized that they

00:40:57.070 --> 00:40:58.570 align:middle line:84%
had to get to the
very bottom of it.

00:40:58.570 --> 00:41:01.350 align:middle line:84%
I've got to get to the bottom
of what it means to exist.

00:41:01.350 --> 00:41:05.360 align:middle line:84%
And when-- and it's--
and we can do that.

00:41:05.360 --> 00:41:08.365 align:middle line:84%
And the greatest luminaries,
spiritual luminaries

00:41:08.365 --> 00:41:10.490 align:middle line:84%
throughout history, are
individuals, men and women,

00:41:10.490 --> 00:41:11.865 align:middle line:84%
who are kind of
spiritual heroes.

00:41:11.865 --> 00:41:15.820 align:middle line:84%
They've broken through to a
level of depth of experience

00:41:15.820 --> 00:41:18.550 align:middle line:84%
and perspective
and understanding,

00:41:18.550 --> 00:41:21.710 align:middle line:84%
where they really know,
where they're grounded.

00:41:21.710 --> 00:41:24.490 align:middle line:84%
They're grounded at a level of
depth that, for most people,

00:41:24.490 --> 00:41:25.305 align:middle line:90%
is unimaginable.

00:41:25.305 --> 00:41:26.690 align:middle line:90%


00:41:26.690 --> 00:41:30.490 align:middle line:84%
And so I think that are the
spiritual practices that we

00:41:30.490 --> 00:41:32.905 align:middle line:84%
do, assuming we're
doing any, are

00:41:32.905 --> 00:41:38.610 align:middle line:84%
as powerful as is our
aspiration to truly become

00:41:38.610 --> 00:41:40.550 align:middle line:84%
a liberated,
transformed individual.

00:41:40.550 --> 00:41:44.117 align:middle line:84%
In other words, a lot of us,
we're already on a trajectory.

00:41:44.117 --> 00:41:44.950 align:middle line:90%
We're already going.

00:41:44.950 --> 00:41:45.650 align:middle line:90%
We're very busy.

00:41:45.650 --> 00:41:47.410 align:middle line:84%
And we want to find
a way to feel better

00:41:47.410 --> 00:41:48.840 align:middle line:90%
doing what we're already doing.

00:41:48.840 --> 00:41:51.680 align:middle line:84%
When the question is maybe we
don't know what the heck we're

00:41:51.680 --> 00:41:56.590 align:middle line:84%
doing, and there might be
a much more wholesome, more

00:41:56.590 --> 00:41:58.550 align:middle line:84%
philosophically profound
and spiritually honest

00:41:58.550 --> 00:42:01.050 align:middle line:84%
relationship to life that we
have to be willing to consider.

00:42:01.050 --> 00:42:02.130 align:middle line:90%


00:42:02.130 --> 00:42:04.640 align:middle line:84%
But most people are afraid
to think too deeply,

00:42:04.640 --> 00:42:07.080 align:middle line:84%
to question too deeply,
to ask questions

00:42:07.080 --> 00:42:09.830 align:middle line:84%
that are too big because
they might find out

00:42:09.830 --> 00:42:11.230 align:middle line:90%
that they've made wrong choices.

00:42:11.230 --> 00:42:13.105 align:middle line:84%
But I mean, we have to
be willing to do that.

00:42:13.105 --> 00:42:14.750 align:middle line:84%
We have to be willing
to ask ourselves

00:42:14.750 --> 00:42:16.460 align:middle line:84%
those kind of
questions, you know.

00:42:16.460 --> 00:42:18.069 align:middle line:90%
We want to get on solid ground.

00:42:18.069 --> 00:42:19.860 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So maybe the
questions or the goals

00:42:19.860 --> 00:42:22.190 align:middle line:84%
of making more money, or
getting to the bigger house,

00:42:22.190 --> 00:42:24.180 align:middle line:84%
or climbing the corporate
ladder, or whatever those goals

00:42:24.180 --> 00:42:25.805 align:middle line:84%
and aspirations are,
when you get there

00:42:25.805 --> 00:42:28.676 align:middle line:84%
and you find emptiness, you
realize that that's not really

00:42:28.676 --> 00:42:29.550 align:middle line:90%
the true goal at all.

00:42:29.550 --> 00:42:30.966 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well
that's what we hear.

00:42:30.966 --> 00:42:33.700 align:middle line:84%
We hear, you know-- it hasn't
been my experience in life,

00:42:33.700 --> 00:42:36.920 align:middle line:84%
but we hear from
people who have thought

00:42:36.920 --> 00:42:40.500 align:middle line:84%
that wealth, enormous wealth,
would give them happiness.

00:42:40.500 --> 00:42:42.270 align:middle line:84%
Apparently they find
that it's not true,

00:42:42.270 --> 00:42:43.910 align:middle line:84%
that wealth and
power, especially

00:42:43.910 --> 00:42:47.155 align:middle line:84%
for thoughtful, sensitive
people, doesn't liberate.

00:42:47.155 --> 00:42:48.462 align:middle line:90%


00:42:48.462 --> 00:42:49.465 align:middle line:90%
And quite the opposite.

00:42:49.465 --> 00:42:53.060 align:middle line:84%
It can-- also can create
enormous anxiety and confusion.

00:42:53.060 --> 00:42:56.640 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: This, yes, duality
ultimately, dualism.

00:42:56.640 --> 00:42:57.750 align:middle line:90%


00:42:57.750 --> 00:42:59.270 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: Dualism or worse.

00:42:59.270 --> 00:43:02.560 align:middle line:84%
And so I think the fundamental
thing we're speaking about here

00:43:02.560 --> 00:43:03.680 align:middle line:90%
is just finding a way.

00:43:03.680 --> 00:43:06.350 align:middle line:84%
Just using spiritual techniques
or teachings as a way

00:43:06.350 --> 00:43:09.545 align:middle line:84%
simply to calm down, I
think, is not really enough.

00:43:09.545 --> 00:43:12.440 align:middle line:84%
We have to be willing
to make the effort

00:43:12.440 --> 00:43:16.630 align:middle line:84%
to want to really break through
to something very profound

00:43:16.630 --> 00:43:20.820 align:middle line:84%
that will realign our
relationship to existence

00:43:20.820 --> 00:43:25.140 align:middle line:84%
in a fundamental way, a
fundamental realignment

00:43:25.140 --> 00:43:29.390 align:middle line:84%
in which we become
deeply grounded in life,

00:43:29.390 --> 00:43:32.570 align:middle line:84%
and in being, and in the
knowledge of who we are

00:43:32.570 --> 00:43:33.700 align:middle line:90%
and why we're here.

00:43:33.700 --> 00:43:36.000 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And to do that, we
have to basically realize

00:43:36.000 --> 00:43:39.440 align:middle line:84%
where we are as a society
and then get to that point,

00:43:39.440 --> 00:43:43.260 align:middle line:84%
because several of us don't even
know that that level exists.

00:43:43.260 --> 00:43:44.854 align:middle line:84%
So we're going to
take a quick break.

00:43:44.854 --> 00:43:46.770 align:middle line:84%
When we come back, we're
going to explore more

00:43:46.770 --> 00:43:50.530 align:middle line:84%
about how to live with
non-duality and non-separatism

00:43:50.530 --> 00:43:52.427 align:middle line:84%
when we come back with
my guest Andrew Cohen.

00:43:52.427 --> 00:43:53.260 align:middle line:90%
We'll be right back.

00:43:53.260 --> 00:44:01.110 align:middle line:90%


00:44:01.110 --> 00:44:01.780 align:middle line:90%
Welcome back.

00:44:01.780 --> 00:44:03.420 align:middle line:84%
My guest is Andrew
Cohen, and we're

00:44:03.420 --> 00:44:07.020 align:middle line:84%
talking about practical and
evolutionary enlightenment.

00:44:07.020 --> 00:44:09.120 align:middle line:84%
And we were talking
before the break

00:44:09.120 --> 00:44:12.740 align:middle line:84%
about how to take the
concepts of non-duality

00:44:12.740 --> 00:44:15.200 align:middle line:84%
and apply it to
our everyday life.

00:44:15.200 --> 00:44:18.230 align:middle line:84%
And how do you have
goals and aspirations

00:44:18.230 --> 00:44:21.130 align:middle line:84%
when you're realizing that
everything is interconnected?

00:44:21.130 --> 00:44:25.700 align:middle line:84%
So you explained that we're
in this era of a postmodern

00:44:25.700 --> 00:44:26.230 align:middle line:90%
predicament.

00:44:26.230 --> 00:44:28.170 align:middle line:84%
Can you tell us a
little bit about that?

00:44:28.170 --> 00:44:29.930 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, the
whole notion of what

00:44:29.930 --> 00:44:33.210 align:middle line:84%
I call the postmodern
predicament is

00:44:33.210 --> 00:44:36.960 align:middle line:84%
that since the '60s
generation-- I'm a baby boomer.

00:44:36.960 --> 00:44:38.290 align:middle line:90%
I'm 56.

00:44:38.290 --> 00:44:42.104 align:middle line:84%
And you look like you're maybe
next generation after me.

00:44:42.104 --> 00:44:43.270 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Getting there, yeah.

00:44:43.270 --> 00:44:43.454 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: Yeah.

00:44:43.454 --> 00:44:45.037 align:middle line:84%
But so starting with
the baby boomers,

00:44:45.037 --> 00:44:46.810 align:middle line:84%
the postwar generation,
and our children,

00:44:46.810 --> 00:44:48.710 align:middle line:84%
and our children's
children, we fall

00:44:48.710 --> 00:44:51.190 align:middle line:84%
into the category of whom I
call the luckiest people that

00:44:51.190 --> 00:44:52.370 align:middle line:90%
have ever been born.

00:44:52.370 --> 00:44:54.680 align:middle line:84%
We are-- We
experience a standard

00:44:54.680 --> 00:44:57.920 align:middle line:84%
of living that's historically
unprecedented-- wealth,

00:44:57.920 --> 00:45:00.000 align:middle line:84%
comfort, a level
of education that's

00:45:00.000 --> 00:45:01.620 align:middle line:90%
historically unprecedented.

00:45:01.620 --> 00:45:05.470 align:middle line:84%
We have freedom of thought,
freedom of opinion,

00:45:05.470 --> 00:45:06.550 align:middle line:90%
freedom of movement.

00:45:06.550 --> 00:45:07.492 align:middle line:90%


00:45:07.492 --> 00:45:09.700 align:middle line:84%
Most of us can more or less
do anything that we want.

00:45:09.700 --> 00:45:11.830 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: We could travel
wherever we want.

00:45:11.830 --> 00:45:12.970 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Within reason,
we can more or less

00:45:12.970 --> 00:45:13.928 align:middle line:90%
do anything we imagine.

00:45:13.928 --> 00:45:14.930 align:middle line:90%


00:45:14.930 --> 00:45:16.930 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Now, you're talking
about-- those things

00:45:16.930 --> 00:45:19.400 align:middle line:84%
that you're saying with access
to education, and access

00:45:19.400 --> 00:45:21.316 align:middle line:84%
to higher education, and
so forth, all of this

00:45:21.316 --> 00:45:22.090 align:middle line:90%
requires money.

00:45:22.090 --> 00:45:22.870 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: Yeah.

00:45:22.870 --> 00:45:24.453 align:middle line:84%
But what I'm saying
is there are many,

00:45:24.453 --> 00:45:27.210 align:middle line:84%
many-- there's many, many, many,
many of us, billions of us,

00:45:27.210 --> 00:45:27.710 align:middle line:90%
right?

00:45:27.710 --> 00:45:30.350 align:middle line:84%
And so it starts with
the postwar generation,

00:45:30.350 --> 00:45:33.240 align:middle line:84%
the baby boomer generation,
our children, our children's

00:45:33.240 --> 00:45:36.074 align:middle line:84%
children fall into the category
of, historically speaking,

00:45:36.074 --> 00:45:37.490 align:middle line:84%
the luckiest people
that have ever

00:45:37.490 --> 00:45:39.480 align:middle line:84%
been born in the history
of human civilization

00:45:39.480 --> 00:45:41.271 align:middle line:84%
for all the reasons
that we just described.

00:45:41.271 --> 00:45:42.130 align:middle line:90%


00:45:42.130 --> 00:45:44.450 align:middle line:84%
And what's interesting--
what's interesting

00:45:44.450 --> 00:45:46.500 align:middle line:84%
is that, objectively,
it's true we

00:45:46.500 --> 00:45:48.890 align:middle line:84%
are luckier than any other
group of human beings

00:45:48.890 --> 00:45:50.250 align:middle line:90%
that's ever been born.

00:45:50.250 --> 00:45:53.907 align:middle line:84%
But we don't seem to feel lucky,
or we don't seem to know that--

00:45:53.907 --> 00:45:54.490 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:45:54.490 --> 00:45:54.770 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: --we're the luckiest.

00:45:54.770 --> 00:45:55.900 align:middle line:90%
And that's the problem.

00:45:55.900 --> 00:46:00.331 align:middle line:84%
And if you get to know a lot of
these so-called luckiest people

00:46:00.331 --> 00:46:01.830 align:middle line:84%
that have ever been
born, if you get

00:46:01.830 --> 00:46:03.996 align:middle line:84%
to know what their inner
lives are like, a lot of us

00:46:03.996 --> 00:46:08.870 align:middle line:84%
feel-- experience alienation,
existential confusion,

00:46:08.870 --> 00:46:11.129 align:middle line:84%
victimization, a lot
of victimization.

00:46:11.129 --> 00:46:11.920 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Loneliness.

00:46:11.920 --> 00:46:13.378 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Loneliness
and insecurity.

00:46:13.378 --> 00:46:17.530 align:middle line:84%
And so that creates quite a--
there's quite an irony in that,

00:46:17.530 --> 00:46:20.280 align:middle line:84%
that the luckiest people
that have ever been born

00:46:20.280 --> 00:46:23.010 align:middle line:84%
in the history of human
civilization generally

00:46:23.010 --> 00:46:25.730 align:middle line:84%
don't recognize the fact that
they're the luckiest people

00:46:25.730 --> 00:46:25.940 align:middle line:90%
that have ever been born--

00:46:25.940 --> 00:46:27.220 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: We're still
trying to achieve--

00:46:27.220 --> 00:46:28.360 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: --and don't
feel very lucky.

00:46:28.360 --> 00:46:28.560 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: No.

00:46:28.560 --> 00:46:29.910 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: And so
that's a very big part

00:46:29.910 --> 00:46:31.160 align:middle line:90%
of the postmodern predicament.

00:46:31.160 --> 00:46:32.470 align:middle line:90%


00:46:32.470 --> 00:46:34.930 align:middle line:84%
And I think that the
solution to this-- this

00:46:34.930 --> 00:46:36.720 align:middle line:90%
is a cultural epidemic.

00:46:36.720 --> 00:46:38.460 align:middle line:90%
It's not a personal problem.

00:46:38.460 --> 00:46:41.590 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, so how do
you create the future,

00:46:41.590 --> 00:46:45.135 align:middle line:84%
where-- and how does
that relate to evolution?

00:46:45.135 --> 00:46:47.350 align:middle line:84%
How do you-- I mean,
we're into this place

00:46:47.350 --> 00:46:50.470 align:middle line:84%
of constantly wanting to
improve the quality of our lives

00:46:50.470 --> 00:46:52.500 align:middle line:84%
through this, that,
and the other thing.

00:46:52.500 --> 00:46:56.720 align:middle line:84%
How do you go towards the future
and still create this feeling

00:46:56.720 --> 00:46:57.304 align:middle line:90%
of--?

00:46:57.304 --> 00:46:59.720 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, there's one
other element to the postmodern

00:46:59.720 --> 00:47:01.855 align:middle line:84%
predicament, which
is that in the '60s,

00:47:01.855 --> 00:47:04.210 align:middle line:84%
there was-- the cultural
revolutions that

00:47:04.210 --> 00:47:06.210 align:middle line:84%
were so dramatic and
extraordinary that happened

00:47:06.210 --> 00:47:08.540 align:middle line:84%
in the 1960s were all
about-- it was all about

00:47:08.540 --> 00:47:10.460 align:middle line:84%
liberation, liberation
of the individual.

00:47:10.460 --> 00:47:10.810 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:47:10.810 --> 00:47:12.970 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: And so this gave rise
to the women's movement, which

00:47:12.970 --> 00:47:14.860 align:middle line:84%
was such a profoundly
progressive step

00:47:14.860 --> 00:47:17.460 align:middle line:90%
forward for culture.

00:47:17.460 --> 00:47:19.660 align:middle line:84%
And there was the
Civil Rights Movement

00:47:19.660 --> 00:47:22.000 align:middle line:84%
for the equal rights
for any individual.

00:47:22.000 --> 00:47:23.927 align:middle line:84%
And there was also
the Me Generation.

00:47:23.927 --> 00:47:24.760 align:middle line:90%
It was all about me.

00:47:24.760 --> 00:47:26.420 align:middle line:90%
And I grew up in that time.

00:47:26.420 --> 00:47:28.100 align:middle line:84%
My parents said,
sweetheart, you should

00:47:28.100 --> 00:47:29.570 align:middle line:84%
do whatever is going
to make you happy.

00:47:29.570 --> 00:47:29.820 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:47:29.820 --> 00:47:30.910 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: And my
teachers told me,

00:47:30.910 --> 00:47:32.993 align:middle line:84%
you should do whatever is
going to make you happy.

00:47:32.993 --> 00:47:36.670 align:middle line:84%
So I, like many of my-- like
many others from my generation,

00:47:36.670 --> 00:47:39.200 align:middle line:84%
I just grew thinking that
the world was my oyster.

00:47:39.200 --> 00:47:41.690 align:middle line:84%
Nobody ever told me
that I had an obligation

00:47:41.690 --> 00:47:42.910 align:middle line:90%
to anyone or anything.

00:47:42.910 --> 00:47:43.990 align:middle line:90%


00:47:43.990 --> 00:47:46.136 align:middle line:84%
I just simply looked
at life at how--

00:47:46.136 --> 00:47:48.790 align:middle line:84%
what was I going to do that
was going to make me happy.

00:47:48.790 --> 00:47:51.070 align:middle line:84%
And this has created a
culture of narcissism.

00:47:51.070 --> 00:47:54.060 align:middle line:84%
And my generation
tends to be-- we

00:47:54.060 --> 00:47:56.080 align:middle line:90%
tend to be very narcissistic.

00:47:56.080 --> 00:47:58.892 align:middle line:84%
Our children-- Our children
tend to be very narcissistic.

00:47:58.892 --> 00:48:00.850 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Don't you think
the Millennials and all

00:48:00.850 --> 00:48:02.650 align:middle line:84%
the generations right
now tend to be that way?

00:48:02.650 --> 00:48:04.680 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, it's
largely for these reasons.

00:48:04.680 --> 00:48:06.320 align:middle line:84%
And so the postmodern
predicament

00:48:06.320 --> 00:48:08.270 align:middle line:84%
is both that we're the luckiest
people that have ever been born

00:48:08.270 --> 00:48:09.900 align:middle line:84%
and we don't know
it, plus the fact

00:48:09.900 --> 00:48:12.820 align:middle line:84%
that we have grown up in a
culture of narcissism, which

00:48:12.820 --> 00:48:15.300 align:middle line:84%
tends to have made
us very profoundly

00:48:15.300 --> 00:48:17.055 align:middle line:84%
self-centered and
self-concerned.

00:48:17.055 --> 00:48:19.420 align:middle line:84%
And a narcissistic
individual is someone

00:48:19.420 --> 00:48:22.000 align:middle line:90%
who thinks about me 24/7.

00:48:22.000 --> 00:48:22.680 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Only me.

00:48:22.680 --> 00:48:23.600 align:middle line:90%
How is it going to work for me?

00:48:23.600 --> 00:48:24.110 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: Yeah, and right.

00:48:24.110 --> 00:48:25.230 align:middle line:90%
And I always tell people--

00:48:25.230 --> 00:48:26.070 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: How does
that apply to me?

00:48:26.070 --> 00:48:26.660 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: Yeah, yeah.

00:48:26.660 --> 00:48:28.210 align:middle line:84%
But I always tell people
it's not a personal problem.

00:48:28.210 --> 00:48:29.251 align:middle line:90%
It's a cultural epidemic.

00:48:29.251 --> 00:48:30.789 align:middle line:90%
And so what do we do about this?

00:48:30.789 --> 00:48:32.330 align:middle line:84%
So psychotherapy is
not going to help

00:48:32.330 --> 00:48:33.955 align:middle line:84%
us deal with the
problem of narcissism.

00:48:33.955 --> 00:48:35.120 align:middle line:90%


00:48:35.120 --> 00:48:40.440 align:middle line:84%
And so I think that,
to me, that human life,

00:48:40.440 --> 00:48:44.655 align:middle line:84%
if it's not connected to a deep
source of meaning and purpose--

00:48:44.655 --> 00:48:48.979 align:middle line:84%
in other words, that my--
without it being connected with

00:48:48.979 --> 00:48:50.520 align:middle line:84%
a deep source of
meaning and purpose,

00:48:50.520 --> 00:48:53.177 align:middle line:84%
we're going to find
ourself adrift,

00:48:53.177 --> 00:48:55.260 align:middle line:84%
experiencing all the things
we spoke about before,

00:48:55.260 --> 00:48:56.259 align:middle line:90%
alienation--

00:48:56.259 --> 00:48:57.050 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Loneliness.

00:48:57.050 --> 00:48:58.280 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: --alienation,
loneliness.

00:48:58.280 --> 00:48:59.090 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Achieving the dream
and never getting there.

00:48:59.090 --> 00:49:02.030 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: And also existential
confusion, like why am I here?

00:49:02.030 --> 00:49:03.960 align:middle line:84%
Some people even say, I
didn't ask to be born.

00:49:03.960 --> 00:49:05.585 align:middle line:84%
I don't even know if
I want to be here.

00:49:05.585 --> 00:49:07.465 align:middle line:84%
I mean, outrageous
things like that.

00:49:07.465 --> 00:49:09.055 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And shallower
relationships.

00:49:09.055 --> 00:49:10.680 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well,
shallower relationships.

00:49:10.680 --> 00:49:13.870 align:middle line:84%
And for example, now, for
example, with birth control,

00:49:13.870 --> 00:49:16.620 align:middle line:84%
many people choose
to have children

00:49:16.620 --> 00:49:18.500 align:middle line:84%
because they feel,
if I have a child,

00:49:18.500 --> 00:49:20.090 align:middle line:84%
it will give me a
sense of purpose.

00:49:20.090 --> 00:49:22.048 align:middle line:84%
And there's nothing wrong
with having children.

00:49:22.048 --> 00:49:24.540 align:middle line:84%
It's a wonderful and a
good thing to have-- to do.

00:49:24.540 --> 00:49:26.820 align:middle line:84%
But if people have
children because they

00:49:26.820 --> 00:49:29.503 align:middle line:84%
don't feel a sense
of purpose, it

00:49:29.503 --> 00:49:33.730 align:middle line:84%
doesn't seem to be-- it's a sign
that, at the level of culture,

00:49:33.730 --> 00:49:35.360 align:middle line:90%
something's missing.

00:49:35.360 --> 00:49:38.440 align:middle line:84%
And so I-- to me-- so
therefore, the solution

00:49:38.440 --> 00:49:40.970 align:middle line:84%
to this postmodern
predicament is

00:49:40.970 --> 00:49:44.740 align:middle line:84%
the discovery of a non-relative
or an absolute context,

00:49:44.740 --> 00:49:47.590 align:middle line:84%
a big source of meaning
for why I'm here

00:49:47.590 --> 00:49:49.060 align:middle line:90%
and for why you're here.

00:49:49.060 --> 00:49:51.190 align:middle line:84%
And if we don't discover
a bigger sense of purpose

00:49:51.190 --> 00:49:53.640 align:middle line:84%
for why I exist,
for why you exist,

00:49:53.640 --> 00:49:57.209 align:middle line:84%
we're going to be looking
for more relative ways

00:49:57.209 --> 00:49:59.000 align:middle line:84%
to find a source of
meaning that ultimately

00:49:59.000 --> 00:49:59.950 align:middle line:90%
aren't going to do it.

00:49:59.950 --> 00:50:01.730 align:middle line:90%
I mean, human beings have been--

00:50:01.730 --> 00:50:03.310 align:middle line:90%


00:50:03.310 --> 00:50:05.410 align:middle line:84%
And so I think the
answer to that question

00:50:05.410 --> 00:50:08.600 align:middle line:84%
is, I think, now in
the 21st century,

00:50:08.600 --> 00:50:09.850 align:middle line:90%
is the awakening to evolution.

00:50:09.850 --> 00:50:12.790 align:middle line:84%
Evolution's the biggest new
idea in the last 200 years.

00:50:12.790 --> 00:50:15.510 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So it gets us out
of a place of narcissism

00:50:15.510 --> 00:50:17.424 align:middle line:84%
and into an evolutionary
conversation.

00:50:17.424 --> 00:50:18.840 align:middle line:84%
You're saying
that's the solution?

00:50:18.840 --> 00:50:20.465 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, because
the question is,

00:50:20.465 --> 00:50:23.380 align:middle line:84%
well, we want to blow open
the context of my life.

00:50:23.380 --> 00:50:26.050 align:middle line:84%
So if my life is all about
me and my personal fears

00:50:26.050 --> 00:50:29.130 align:middle line:84%
and personal desires, the
context is completely narrow.

00:50:29.130 --> 00:50:30.540 align:middle line:84%
Everything that
happens is all in

00:50:30.540 --> 00:50:33.240 align:middle line:84%
this small, self-referential--
self-referencing.

00:50:33.240 --> 00:50:34.270 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Survivalistic.

00:50:34.270 --> 00:50:36.145 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: But it's a
bubble of self-reference.

00:50:36.145 --> 00:50:36.606 align:middle line:90%


00:50:36.606 --> 00:50:37.980 align:middle line:84%
So when you start
teaching people

00:50:37.980 --> 00:50:42.600 align:middle line:84%
about what science has
discovered about who we are,

00:50:42.600 --> 00:50:44.130 align:middle line:90%
it blows people's minds.

00:50:44.130 --> 00:50:46.020 align:middle line:84%
And so what that
means is that we're

00:50:46.020 --> 00:50:49.110 align:middle line:84%
part of a process, a
cosmic process, that

00:50:49.110 --> 00:50:52.180 align:middle line:84%
blew into existence
14 billion years ago.

00:50:52.180 --> 00:50:53.330 align:middle line:90%


00:50:53.330 --> 00:50:56.830 align:middle line:84%
And it's a great mystery that
out of no thing whatsoever,

00:50:56.830 --> 00:51:01.010 align:middle line:84%
there was this huge,
cosmic explosion, which

00:51:01.010 --> 00:51:02.470 align:middle line:90%
gave rise to matter and energy.

00:51:02.470 --> 00:51:04.080 align:middle line:90%


00:51:04.080 --> 00:51:06.550 align:middle line:84%
Matter and energy
gave rise to life.

00:51:06.550 --> 00:51:10.290 align:middle line:84%
And life gave rise to
mind and consciousness,

00:51:10.290 --> 00:51:15.290 align:middle line:84%
self-consciousness,
subjectivity, interiority,

00:51:15.290 --> 00:51:16.055 align:middle line:90%
and mind.

00:51:16.055 --> 00:51:17.750 align:middle line:90%


00:51:17.750 --> 00:51:19.910 align:middle line:84%
And the thing about--
when we realize

00:51:19.910 --> 00:51:22.220 align:middle line:84%
that, we begin to see--
our sense of history

00:51:22.220 --> 00:51:25.621 align:middle line:84%
begins to go from just
me and my personal life--

00:51:25.621 --> 00:51:27.370 align:middle line:84%
and not just the history
of me personally,

00:51:27.370 --> 00:51:29.190 align:middle line:84%
not just this
history of my family

00:51:29.190 --> 00:51:33.720 align:middle line:84%
or my ethnic group or my nation,
but the history of the cosmos

00:51:33.720 --> 00:51:38.210 align:middle line:84%
then relates to my experience
of my physical experience,

00:51:38.210 --> 00:51:41.100 align:middle line:84%
my biological experience, my
experience of consciousness

00:51:41.100 --> 00:51:43.150 align:middle line:84%
and cognition that relates
back to the beginning

00:51:43.150 --> 00:51:43.870 align:middle line:90%
of the universe.

00:51:43.870 --> 00:51:47.620 align:middle line:84%
I realize that the-- that all
of my exper-- all the experience

00:51:47.620 --> 00:51:53.220 align:middle line:84%
I'm having right now
is inherently related

00:51:53.220 --> 00:51:57.776 align:middle line:84%
to the creative process,
right, that my body is made up

00:51:57.776 --> 00:52:01.140 align:middle line:84%
of atoms and
molecules, that we're

00:52:01.140 --> 00:52:03.630 align:middle line:84%
born at the very
beginning of this process.

00:52:03.630 --> 00:52:06.550 align:middle line:84%
I realize that my
mind and capacity

00:52:06.550 --> 00:52:08.820 align:middle line:84%
for thinking about life
and assuming perspectives

00:52:08.820 --> 00:52:11.830 align:middle line:84%
is related to the
evolution of human culture.

00:52:11.830 --> 00:52:15.910 align:middle line:84%
That my aspiration to want
to become more conscious

00:52:15.910 --> 00:52:18.120 align:middle line:84%
is related to the fact that
the universe is actually

00:52:18.120 --> 00:52:20.460 align:middle line:84%
trying to evolve at the
level of consciousness.

00:52:20.460 --> 00:52:23.360 align:middle line:84%
And when you experience the
spiritual impulse, which

00:52:23.360 --> 00:52:25.290 align:middle line:84%
is the aspiration to
become more conscious,

00:52:25.290 --> 00:52:29.830 align:middle line:84%
you realize, well,
who I am is really

00:52:29.830 --> 00:52:32.212 align:middle line:84%
the energy and intelligence
that created the universe

00:52:32.212 --> 00:52:33.420 align:middle line:90%
and is creating the universe.

00:52:33.420 --> 00:52:34.500 align:middle line:90%
It's called Eros.

00:52:34.500 --> 00:52:35.660 align:middle line:90%
It's the drive to exist.

00:52:35.660 --> 00:52:37.368 align:middle line:84%
It's the creative
motive in the universe.

00:52:37.368 --> 00:52:38.410 align:middle line:90%


00:52:38.410 --> 00:52:42.690 align:middle line:84%
And that motive is trying to
understand itself, know itself,

00:52:42.690 --> 00:52:45.720 align:middle line:84%
realize itself, recognize
itself, and give rise to itself

00:52:45.720 --> 00:52:47.227 align:middle line:90%
through me in my best moments.

00:52:47.227 --> 00:52:49.310 align:middle line:84%
And I realize, well, that's
what's happening here,

00:52:49.310 --> 00:52:51.445 align:middle line:84%
that this body, this
mind, this personality,

00:52:51.445 --> 00:52:53.690 align:middle line:90%
is a sh-- this is a sheath.

00:52:53.690 --> 00:52:54.956 align:middle line:90%
The body's a sheath.

00:52:54.956 --> 00:52:56.455 align:middle line:84%
The mind and the
personality are a--

00:52:56.455 --> 00:52:59.930 align:middle line:84%
or is a sheath through which
the energy and intelligence that

00:52:59.930 --> 00:53:03.280 align:middle line:84%
created the universe and
is creating the universe

00:53:03.280 --> 00:53:04.500 align:middle line:90%
can engage with itself.

00:53:04.500 --> 00:53:05.866 align:middle line:90%


00:53:05.866 --> 00:53:08.140 align:middle line:84%
That human-- with
human consciousness,

00:53:08.140 --> 00:53:10.560 align:middle line:84%
with highly evolved
human consciousness,

00:53:10.560 --> 00:53:13.650 align:middle line:84%
evolution can become
conscious of itself.

00:53:13.650 --> 00:53:16.320 align:middle line:90%
Evolution awakens to itself.

00:53:16.320 --> 00:53:19.880 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So there's no space
for narcissism in evolution.

00:53:19.880 --> 00:53:22.920 align:middle line:84%
There's no space for survival,
really, in evolution,

00:53:22.920 --> 00:53:25.770 align:middle line:84%
if you are taking this
concept of the stress

00:53:25.770 --> 00:53:27.800 align:middle line:90%
that we are experiencing.

00:53:27.800 --> 00:53:31.180 align:middle line:84%
And you gave me a
great answer earlier

00:53:31.180 --> 00:53:33.090 align:middle line:84%
about the internal
stress that we

00:53:33.090 --> 00:53:36.360 align:middle line:84%
feel that we're experiencing
is actually creative stress.

00:53:36.360 --> 00:53:38.310 align:middle line:84%
And if you could reframe
the whole concept

00:53:38.310 --> 00:53:41.262 align:middle line:84%
into this creative
stress, that is a great--

00:53:41.262 --> 00:53:43.720 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, there's positive
stress and negative stress.

00:53:43.720 --> 00:53:46.107 align:middle line:84%
So in other words,
for example, if, you

00:53:46.107 --> 00:53:48.050 align:middle line:84%
know-- if you,
for example, let's

00:53:48.050 --> 00:53:50.470 align:middle line:84%
say you're trying to-- you
want to run up a mountain,

00:53:50.470 --> 00:53:52.520 align:middle line:84%
or you want to run a
marathon or something.

00:53:52.520 --> 00:53:55.200 align:middle line:84%
And so then you--
that's gonna take-- you

00:53:55.200 --> 00:53:58.521 align:middle line:84%
are going to engage
with enormous stress

00:53:58.521 --> 00:53:59.770 align:middle line:90%
in order to achieve your goal.

00:53:59.770 --> 00:54:04.370 align:middle line:84%
But it's positive
because you're trying

00:54:04.370 --> 00:54:07.099 align:middle line:84%
to be able to do something that
maybe you've never done before.

00:54:07.099 --> 00:54:09.140 align:middle line:84%
So it's-- what you're
doing is very constructive.

00:54:09.140 --> 00:54:12.600 align:middle line:84%
And so because you're trying
to achieve a goal that you've

