emerge from life?

01:11:42.360 --> 01:11:44.870 align:middle line:84%
And so those are examples
of these three big bangs,

01:11:44.870 --> 01:11:47.340 align:middle line:84%
or these three leaps in
the creative process,

01:11:47.340 --> 01:11:50.720 align:middle line:84%
these extraordinary leaps
that defy our understanding.

01:11:50.720 --> 01:11:52.810 align:middle line:84%
These are leaps
that are-- they're

01:11:52.810 --> 01:11:57.060 align:middle line:84%
quantum leaps in complexity, in
developmental and evolutionary

01:11:57.060 --> 01:12:00.890 align:middle line:84%
complexity, that are
ultimately mysterious.

01:12:00.890 --> 01:12:03.100 align:middle line:84%
And so when we
reali-- when we look

01:12:03.100 --> 01:12:05.260 align:middle line:84%
back from where we are
to see where we came from

01:12:05.260 --> 01:12:07.670 align:middle line:84%
and we see that we're
a product of emergence,

01:12:07.670 --> 01:12:10.310 align:middle line:84%
that we are emergence
in progress,

01:12:10.310 --> 01:12:13.502 align:middle line:84%
and we realize that the
future of the evolution

01:12:13.502 --> 01:12:15.210 align:middle line:84%
of the universe, which
is going to happen

01:12:15.210 --> 01:12:18.790 align:middle line:84%
at the level of culture,
is going to depend upon you

01:12:18.790 --> 01:12:22.681 align:middle line:84%
and me, we're going to need
to assume a relationship

01:12:22.681 --> 01:12:24.180 align:middle line:84%
to the human
experience that's going

01:12:24.180 --> 01:12:26.150 align:middle line:84%
to make it possible
for creative leaps

01:12:26.150 --> 01:12:27.641 align:middle line:90%
forward to happen through us.

01:12:27.641 --> 01:12:28.140 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

01:12:28.140 --> 01:12:30.830 align:middle line:84%
So that is your big,
very big intention.

01:12:30.830 --> 01:12:32.190 align:middle line:90%


01:12:32.190 --> 01:12:34.560 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: It's an inherently
creative relationship

01:12:34.560 --> 01:12:37.980 align:middle line:84%
to existence that's not just
about me becoming, learning how

01:12:37.980 --> 01:12:39.650 align:middle line:84%
to paint or learning
how to write.

01:12:39.650 --> 01:12:41.871 align:middle line:84%
It's not only about my
own self actualization.

01:12:41.871 --> 01:12:44.120 align:middle line:84%
It's about the evolution of
the interior of the cosmos

01:12:44.120 --> 01:12:44.990 align:middle line:90%
through me.

01:12:44.990 --> 01:12:47.510 align:middle line:84%
And to me, when you get--
when we get this idea,

01:12:47.510 --> 01:12:51.110 align:middle line:84%
it's the most exciting,
inspiring, thrilling

01:12:51.110 --> 01:12:54.560 align:middle line:84%
recognition of who I am and what
the purpose of existence is.

01:12:54.560 --> 01:12:56.810 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And that takes you
to the second tenant, which

01:12:56.810 --> 01:12:59.155 align:middle line:84%
is that power of volition
to get you to that place.

01:12:59.155 --> 01:12:59.780 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: Right.

01:12:59.780 --> 01:13:03.080 align:middle line:84%
So the first one, then, so then
my intention-- my intention

01:13:03.080 --> 01:13:06.449 align:middle line:84%
then becomes, really, the
evolution of the interior

01:13:06.449 --> 01:13:08.240 align:middle line:84%
of the cosmos, the
evolution of the cosmos,

01:13:08.240 --> 01:13:09.640 align:middle line:90%
the evolution of the world.

01:13:09.640 --> 01:13:12.747 align:middle line:84%
And my reason for existence
is for the evolution

01:13:12.747 --> 01:13:14.330 align:middle line:84%
of the world through
me, the evolution

01:13:14.330 --> 01:13:16.246 align:middle line:84%
of human consciousness
and culture through me,

01:13:16.246 --> 01:13:17.800 align:middle line:84%
which is the evolution
of the cosmos.

01:13:17.800 --> 01:13:20.815 align:middle line:84%
So that shift means, if
you take that seriously,

01:13:20.815 --> 01:13:23.876 align:middle line:84%
if one takes that seriously,
it completely compels

01:13:23.876 --> 01:13:26.250 align:middle line:84%
you to transcend the fears
and desires of the small self,

01:13:26.250 --> 01:13:27.910 align:middle line:84%
the small ego, which
is really worried

01:13:27.910 --> 01:13:28.910 align:middle line:90%
about me and my little life.

01:13:28.910 --> 01:13:30.220 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Where the stress
is, where the stress is.

01:13:30.220 --> 01:13:32.136 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: And suddlenly,
you're realizing, wow,

01:13:32.136 --> 01:13:35.130 align:middle line:84%
this is about living the biggest
life possible for the biggest

01:13:35.130 --> 01:13:35.630 align:middle line:90%
reason.

01:13:35.630 --> 01:13:37.340 align:middle line:84%
So that's what the first
tenant's all about.

01:13:37.340 --> 01:13:38.360 align:middle line:84%
And that's the
most important one.

01:13:38.360 --> 01:13:40.068 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It chunks up,
and it gets you out

01:13:40.068 --> 01:13:41.890 align:middle line:84%
of your current
level of reality.

01:13:41.890 --> 01:13:43.840 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well you start
living big, you know?

01:13:43.840 --> 01:13:46.690 align:middle line:84%
You start living a big
life, not a small life.

01:13:46.690 --> 01:13:47.612 align:middle line:90%
And that takes guts.

01:13:47.612 --> 01:13:48.320 align:middle line:90%
It takes courage.

01:13:48.320 --> 01:13:49.195 align:middle line:90%
It takes inspiration.

01:13:49.195 --> 01:13:50.350 align:middle line:90%


01:13:50.350 --> 01:13:52.650 align:middle line:84%
The law of volitionality
is all about choice.

01:13:52.650 --> 01:13:58.450 align:middle line:84%
It basically says that we
have to transcend the victim

01:13:58.450 --> 01:13:58.950 align:middle line:90%
position.

01:13:58.950 --> 01:14:01.590 align:middle line:84%
We have to get over it
radically, unconditionally,

01:14:01.590 --> 01:14:03.220 align:middle line:90%
once and for all and forever.

01:14:03.220 --> 01:14:06.102 align:middle line:84%
So in order to do that, we
have to take responsibility

01:14:06.102 --> 01:14:07.810 align:middle line:84%
for the consequences
of everything that's

01:14:07.810 --> 01:14:08.660 align:middle line:90%
ever happened to us.

01:14:08.660 --> 01:14:10.550 align:middle line:84%
We've all been hurt,
wounded, traumatized,

01:14:10.550 --> 01:14:12.560 align:middle line:84%
victimized in some
way or shape or form.

01:14:12.560 --> 01:14:14.610 align:middle line:84%
Life is a bumpy ride, like
we were saying before.

01:14:14.610 --> 01:14:17.120 align:middle line:84%
It's full of nicks,
bruises, and scratches.

01:14:17.120 --> 01:14:20.554 align:middle line:84%
And instead of feeling resentful
and blaming other people,

01:14:20.554 --> 01:14:21.970 align:middle line:84%
we have to realize
that, you know,

01:14:21.970 --> 01:14:24.444 align:middle line:84%
life is full of-- everybody's
doing the best they can.

01:14:24.444 --> 01:14:26.360 align:middle line:84%
Life is full of ignorance
and unconsciousness.

01:14:26.360 --> 01:14:27.401 align:middle line:90%
Everybody makes mistakes.

01:14:27.401 --> 01:14:28.570 align:middle line:90%
And people made mistakes.

01:14:28.570 --> 01:14:29.340 align:middle line:90%
I suffered.

01:14:29.340 --> 01:14:29.930 align:middle line:90%
You suffered.

01:14:29.930 --> 01:14:31.680 align:middle line:90%
Other people have suffered.

01:14:31.680 --> 01:14:34.030 align:middle line:84%
The consequences of
all that's my problem.

01:14:34.030 --> 01:14:35.530 align:middle line:90%
It's nobody else's problem.

01:14:35.530 --> 01:14:37.860 align:middle line:84%
My karmic predicament is
my own karmic predicament.

01:14:37.860 --> 01:14:40.465 align:middle line:84%
I blame no one for my own
circumstances, number one.

01:14:40.465 --> 01:14:42.340 align:middle line:84%
And the law of volitionality
says that I also

01:14:42.340 --> 01:14:44.710 align:middle line:84%
have to take responsibility
for all of my own choices.

01:14:44.710 --> 01:14:47.510 align:middle line:84%
My life is my own problem
and my own solution.

01:14:47.510 --> 01:14:50.300 align:middle line:84%
I take unconditional
responsibility for the choices

01:14:50.300 --> 01:14:50.800 align:middle line:90%
that I make.

01:14:50.800 --> 01:14:54.110 align:middle line:84%
I blame no one else for
my life circumstances,

01:14:54.110 --> 01:14:56.520 align:middle line:84%
and I take full
responsibility for my failures

01:14:56.520 --> 01:14:57.700 align:middle line:90%
and my victories.

01:14:57.700 --> 01:14:58.540 align:middle line:90%
It's all me.

01:14:58.540 --> 01:15:01.525 align:middle line:84%
And so this is fully
empowering, you know?

01:15:01.525 --> 01:15:03.800 align:middle line:84%
This is how we get
to a point of sel--

01:15:03.800 --> 01:15:05.675 align:middle line:84%
It points us in the
direction of self mastery

01:15:05.675 --> 01:15:08.110 align:middle line:84%
because we take a radi--
There's a radical sense

01:15:08.110 --> 01:15:11.751 align:middle line:84%
of responsibility we take for
the totality of our condition.

01:15:11.751 --> 01:15:13.250 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I would've
never gotten that

01:15:13.250 --> 01:15:15.240 align:middle line:84%
from the words, the
power of volition,

01:15:15.240 --> 01:15:16.820 align:middle line:84%
until you just
explained it that way.

01:15:16.820 --> 01:15:20.410 align:middle line:84%
Because volition really takes
you into a forward place,

01:15:20.410 --> 01:15:23.380 align:middle line:84%
momentum, moving forward,
rather than getting stuck.

01:15:23.380 --> 01:15:24.970 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, no,
but it also means,

01:15:24.970 --> 01:15:27.100 align:middle line:84%
once we take responsibility
for all that,

01:15:27.100 --> 01:15:30.160 align:middle line:84%
we want to make the right
choices for the right reasons.

01:15:30.160 --> 01:15:32.380 align:middle line:84%
So if I say the most
important thing is

01:15:32.380 --> 01:15:34.620 align:middle line:84%
the evolution of
consciousness and culture,

01:15:34.620 --> 01:15:36.620 align:middle line:84%
then that would mean that
the big choices that I

01:15:36.620 --> 01:15:38.450 align:middle line:84%
make in relationship
to life should

01:15:38.450 --> 01:15:40.460 align:middle line:84%
be expressions of
that big intention.

01:15:40.460 --> 01:15:41.810 align:middle line:90%


01:15:41.810 --> 01:15:42.405 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I see.

01:15:42.405 --> 01:15:42.910 align:middle line:90%
I see.

01:15:42.910 --> 01:15:45.086 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Then my choices
would be expressions

01:15:45.086 --> 01:15:46.710 align:middle line:84%
of that which I said
is most important.

01:15:46.710 --> 01:15:47.450 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

01:15:47.450 --> 01:15:50.180 align:middle line:84%
And so then once you have
found out your intention

01:15:50.180 --> 01:15:53.110 align:middle line:84%
and then move through with
the power of volition,

01:15:53.110 --> 01:15:55.810 align:middle line:84%
then you get into
the third tenant.

01:15:55.810 --> 01:15:59.080 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, OK, so the
third one, the third tenant

01:15:59.080 --> 01:16:00.980 align:middle line:84%
is what I believe
is the ultimate form

01:16:00.980 --> 01:16:01.960 align:middle line:90%
of spiritual practice.

01:16:01.960 --> 01:16:06.730 align:middle line:84%
And all mystical schools point
to the practice of awareness.

01:16:06.730 --> 01:16:09.390 align:middle line:84%
That's really-- All schools,
enlightenment schools

01:16:09.390 --> 01:16:13.090 align:middle line:84%
or mystical schools, tell us
that it's all about cultivating

01:16:13.090 --> 01:16:14.290 align:middle line:90%
the capacity for awareness.

01:16:14.290 --> 01:16:17.320 align:middle line:84%
So the third tenet
says, if you want

01:16:17.320 --> 01:16:19.300 align:middle line:84%
to become an
enlightened human being,

01:16:19.300 --> 01:16:23.290 align:middle line:84%
if you are to be so bold as
to declare that you are going

01:16:23.290 --> 01:16:26.340 align:middle line:84%
to be able to actualize the
evolution of the interior

01:16:26.340 --> 01:16:28.467 align:middle line:84%
of the cosmos, you
have to make sure

01:16:28.467 --> 01:16:30.300 align:middle line:84%
that you're no longer
going to be acting out

01:16:30.300 --> 01:16:31.580 align:middle line:90%
of unconscious motives.

01:16:31.580 --> 01:16:34.720 align:middle line:84%
You have to become an infinitely
more conscious person.

01:16:34.720 --> 01:16:36.610 align:middle line:84%
So the way you
become conscious is

01:16:36.610 --> 01:16:39.340 align:middle line:84%
by paying a lot more attention
to what you're doing.

01:16:39.340 --> 01:16:41.570 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So that's the
awareness of facing everything.

01:16:41.570 --> 01:16:43.480 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, when you face
everything and avoid nothing--

01:16:43.480 --> 01:16:45.359 align:middle line:84%
because often, the
left hand doesn't

01:16:45.359 --> 01:16:47.400 align:middle line:84%
know what the right hand
is doing for many of us.

01:16:47.400 --> 01:16:48.450 align:middle line:90%
We say one thing.

01:16:48.450 --> 01:16:49.060 align:middle line:90%
We do another.

01:16:49.060 --> 01:16:51.310 align:middle line:84%
We don't know how did I end
up in this situation again

01:16:51.310 --> 01:16:52.170 align:middle line:90%
and again and again.

01:16:52.170 --> 01:16:54.430 align:middle line:84%
When I thought I was going
here, I ended up there.

01:16:54.430 --> 01:16:57.190 align:middle line:84%
And the question is because the
self is fundamentally divided,

01:16:57.190 --> 01:16:58.440 align:middle line:90%
consciously and unconsciously.

01:16:58.440 --> 01:17:00.450 align:middle line:90%
We're divided against ourselves.

01:17:00.450 --> 01:17:02.860 align:middle line:84%
And so the idea
here is when you get

01:17:02.860 --> 01:17:06.575 align:middle line:84%
behind this primary intention,
which is the first tenant,

01:17:06.575 --> 01:17:10.064 align:middle line:84%
you can unify yourself
around one motive, right?

01:17:10.064 --> 01:17:12.230 align:middle line:84%
And then when you take
responsibility for all of it,

01:17:12.230 --> 01:17:15.550 align:middle line:84%
you can take responsibility
around this one motive.

01:17:15.550 --> 01:17:18.080 align:middle line:84%
And then how you
stay on track is

01:17:18.080 --> 01:17:21.746 align:middle line:84%
you start paying more
attention than most people do

01:17:21.746 --> 01:17:23.620 align:middle line:84%
to what you're doing
and why you're doing it.

01:17:23.620 --> 01:17:25.769 align:middle line:84%
Because you realize your
choices are important,

01:17:25.769 --> 01:17:27.560 align:middle line:84%
because they're going
to have consequences.

01:17:27.560 --> 01:17:29.876 align:middle line:84%
And if you care, not
just about yourself

01:17:29.876 --> 01:17:32.250 align:middle line:84%
and your own happiness, but
the evolution of the interior

01:17:32.250 --> 01:17:33.916 align:middle line:84%
of the cosmos, the
evolution of culture,

01:17:33.916 --> 01:17:35.490 align:middle line:84%
the evolution of
the world, you have

01:17:35.490 --> 01:17:38.520 align:middle line:84%
to make sure that you
don't make big mistakes

01:17:38.520 --> 01:17:40.386 align:middle line:84%
and that your choices
are a clear expression

01:17:40.386 --> 01:17:41.510 align:middle line:90%
of your highest intentions.

01:17:41.510 --> 01:17:43.570 align:middle line:84%
In order to do that,
there has to be a greater

01:17:43.570 --> 01:17:45.645 align:middle line:84%
degree of awareness
that we bring

01:17:45.645 --> 01:17:48.710 align:middle line:84%
to every single moment, not just
the moments when we're sitting

01:17:48.710 --> 01:17:50.530 align:middle line:84%
in meditation, but
the-- We always

01:17:50.530 --> 01:17:53.270 align:middle line:84%
have to be paying attention
to what am I doing?

01:17:53.270 --> 01:17:54.960 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: How are
we in relationship

01:17:54.960 --> 01:17:55.850 align:middle line:90%
to what we're doing?

01:17:55.850 --> 01:17:58.100 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Yeah, what am I
doing, and why am I doing it?

01:17:58.100 --> 01:17:59.740 align:middle line:84%
And then we all--
we're all crazy.

01:17:59.740 --> 01:18:02.027 align:middle line:90%
The conditioned mind is crazy.

01:18:02.027 --> 01:18:04.110 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What do you mean
by that, we're all crazy?

01:18:04.110 --> 01:18:06.560 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, because--
because if you-- all any of us

01:18:06.560 --> 01:18:10.470 align:middle line:84%
has to do is just monitor
the wandering mind.

01:18:10.470 --> 01:18:13.145 align:middle line:90%
And we're all full of crazy--

01:18:13.145 --> 01:18:14.092 align:middle line:90%


01:18:14.092 --> 01:18:14.800 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Thoughts.

01:18:14.800 --> 01:18:20.200 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: --the crazy thoughts,
crazy desires, crazy fears,

01:18:20.200 --> 01:18:20.850 align:middle line:90%
ambitions.

01:18:20.850 --> 01:18:23.660 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Where does that
stem from, the egoic mind?

01:18:23.660 --> 01:18:26.890 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, it stems from
our biological instincts

01:18:26.890 --> 01:18:31.600 align:middle line:84%
compel us to have-- compel us
in certain directions, which

01:18:31.600 --> 01:18:34.350 align:middle line:84%
is-- you know, which
is-- there is--

01:18:34.350 --> 01:18:36.470 align:middle line:84%
we have-- at least
men, especially,

01:18:36.470 --> 01:18:40.360 align:middle line:84%
have an unending
sexual aspiration,

01:18:40.360 --> 01:18:42.000 align:middle line:90%
which stems from biology.

01:18:42.000 --> 01:18:44.840 align:middle line:84%
So that's one level which,
from a purely rational point

01:18:44.840 --> 01:18:46.730 align:middle line:84%
of view, seems a
little bit crazy.

01:18:46.730 --> 01:18:49.790 align:middle line:84%
There's all-- We can have a
lot of unconscious feelings

01:18:49.790 --> 01:18:55.380 align:middle line:84%
of-- unconscious and conscious
feelings of unworthiness.

01:18:55.380 --> 01:18:58.250 align:middle line:84%
A lot of people feel unworthy,
a lot of self hatred.

01:18:58.250 --> 01:18:59.606 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Mhm.

01:18:59.606 --> 01:19:01.870 align:middle line:90%
Where does that all stem from?

01:19:01.870 --> 01:19:05.235 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, I mean, these
all come from childhood neuroses

01:19:05.235 --> 01:19:08.300 align:middle line:84%
and from-- And it's also
another cultural epidemic.

01:19:08.300 --> 01:19:09.750 align:middle line:90%
So many people feel unworthy.

01:19:09.750 --> 01:19:11.666 align:middle line:84%
The luckiest people that
have ever been born--

01:19:11.666 --> 01:19:14.180 align:middle line:84%
and you have to appreciate the
irony of the luckiest people

01:19:14.180 --> 01:19:16.890 align:middle line:84%
that have been born feeling not
good enough, feeling unworthy.

01:19:16.890 --> 01:19:19.470 align:middle line:84%
And I went through a
lot that in my own life,

01:19:19.470 --> 01:19:21.570 align:middle line:84%
as so many other
people have done.

01:19:21.570 --> 01:19:26.600 align:middle line:84%
Then there can be unwholesome
people, the competitiveness,

01:19:26.600 --> 01:19:29.430 align:middle line:84%
a lack of compassion, a lack
of sympathy with other people,

01:19:29.430 --> 01:19:30.800 align:middle line:90%
a lot of this stuff.

01:19:30.800 --> 01:19:32.370 align:middle line:84%
And it's all-- You
have to understand

01:19:32.370 --> 01:19:34.175 align:middle line:84%
this is all part of
the human experience.

01:19:34.175 --> 01:19:36.050 align:middle line:84%
And the thing is, we
want to get to the point

01:19:36.050 --> 01:19:38.045 align:middle line:84%
where we're so awake
to our higher impulses

01:19:38.045 --> 01:19:39.920 align:middle line:84%
that we're able to bear
witness to this stuff

01:19:39.920 --> 01:19:40.860 align:middle line:90%
without acting out of it.

01:19:40.860 --> 01:19:41.960 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: So you observe it.

01:19:41.960 --> 01:19:42.940 align:middle line:90%
You avoid nothing.

01:19:42.940 --> 01:19:43.360 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: Bear witness.

01:19:43.360 --> 01:19:44.700 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You face it and
observe it and avoid it.

01:19:44.700 --> 01:19:45.020 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: Right.

01:19:45.020 --> 01:19:45.330 align:middle line:90%
Bear witness to it.

01:19:45.330 --> 01:19:46.100 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Don't avoid it.

01:19:46.100 --> 01:19:47.040 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: But don't
act out of it.

01:19:47.040 --> 01:19:48.560 align:middle line:84%
Because the idea
is we don't want

01:19:48.560 --> 01:19:51.082 align:middle line:84%
to start acting out of this
stuff in such a way that's

01:19:51.082 --> 01:19:53.290 align:middle line:84%
going to cause-- have
consequences in the real world.

01:19:53.290 --> 01:19:54.270 align:middle line:90%
And we're going to suffer.

01:19:54.270 --> 01:19:55.350 align:middle line:84%
We and other people
are going to have

01:19:55.350 --> 01:19:56.670 align:middle line:90%
to suffer the consequences.

01:19:56.670 --> 01:19:58.960 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And then that gets us
to the fourth tenant, which is--

01:19:58.960 --> 01:19:59.980 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: But that third
one, the face everything,

01:19:59.980 --> 01:20:02.020 align:middle line:90%
is very-- it's challenging.

01:20:02.020 --> 01:20:03.910 align:middle line:84%
It's the ultimate practice
to face everything

01:20:03.910 --> 01:20:04.743 align:middle line:90%
without avoiding it.

01:20:04.743 --> 01:20:06.320 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I understand
getting stuck

01:20:06.320 --> 01:20:07.831 align:middle line:84%
at that level for
a little while.

01:20:07.831 --> 01:20:10.080 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: The practice of
deep and profound awareness--

01:20:10.080 --> 01:20:11.496 align:middle line:84%
the fourth one
we've been speaking

01:20:11.496 --> 01:20:13.990 align:middle line:84%
about quite a bit
together today.

01:20:13.990 --> 01:20:15.970 align:middle line:84%
And that's the
process perspective.

01:20:15.970 --> 01:20:18.800 align:middle line:84%
And that's realizing--
that's realizing

01:20:18.800 --> 01:20:22.090 align:middle line:84%
that I am and you are
and we all are products

01:20:22.090 --> 01:20:24.490 align:middle line:84%
of a cosmic process that
had a beginning in time

01:20:24.490 --> 01:20:27.620 align:middle line:84%
14 billion years
ago and that we--

01:20:27.620 --> 01:20:31.420 align:middle line:84%
that there was this big cosmic
explosion of energy and matter

01:20:31.420 --> 01:20:34.230 align:middle line:84%
that gave rise to life, that
gave rise to mind, that gave

01:20:34.230 --> 01:20:37.760 align:middle line:84%
rise to culture, that gave
rise to this body, this mind,

01:20:37.760 --> 01:20:42.690 align:middle line:84%
and this personality-- is
an inseparable part this one

01:20:42.690 --> 01:20:43.210 align:middle line:90%
process.

01:20:43.210 --> 01:20:44.860 align:middle line:84%
And so then we begin
to see everything

01:20:44.860 --> 01:20:46.862 align:middle line:84%
I experience in
ter-- everything I

01:20:46.862 --> 01:20:48.320 align:middle line:84%
experience at the
level of biology,

01:20:48.320 --> 01:20:51.099 align:middle line:84%
my physical experience,
my biological experience,

01:20:51.099 --> 01:20:53.265 align:middle line:84%
my psychological experience,
my personal experience,

01:20:53.265 --> 01:20:56.200 align:middle line:84%
that everything happen--
my spiritual experience.

01:20:56.200 --> 01:20:57.770 align:middle line:84%
Everything we
experience internally

01:20:57.770 --> 01:21:00.430 align:middle line:84%
and everything we see externally
that's happening in the world

01:21:00.430 --> 01:21:03.930 align:middle line:84%
is all part and parcel
of this one process.

01:21:03.930 --> 01:21:06.562 align:middle line:84%
It's all one process
that's unfolding.

01:21:06.562 --> 01:21:08.270 align:middle line:84%
So we see everything
from the perspective

01:21:08.270 --> 01:21:10.150 align:middle line:90%
of this one process.

01:21:10.150 --> 01:21:11.830 align:middle line:84%
We don't see just
discrete events.

01:21:11.830 --> 01:21:13.275 align:middle line:90%
My life is not a discrete--

01:21:13.275 --> 01:21:14.685 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's the non duality.

01:21:14.685 --> 01:21:15.310 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: Right.

01:21:15.310 --> 01:21:16.893 align:middle line:84%
In Mahayana Buddhism,
they have what's

01:21:16.893 --> 01:21:18.320 align:middle line:90%
called dependent origination.

01:21:18.320 --> 01:21:21.230 align:middle line:84%
It's the similar idea
that everything exists--

01:21:21.230 --> 01:21:24.580 align:middle line:84%
that exists depends upon
everything else that exists,

01:21:24.580 --> 01:21:25.180 align:middle line:90%
right?

01:21:25.180 --> 01:21:27.170 align:middle line:84%
Everything is dependent
upon everything else.

01:21:27.170 --> 01:21:28.680 align:middle line:84%
And so the unenlightened
perspective

01:21:28.680 --> 01:21:32.390 align:middle line:84%
is the false-- is
imagining falsely

01:21:32.390 --> 01:21:35.020 align:middle line:84%
that I am a discrete event,
you're a discrete event.

01:21:35.020 --> 01:21:37.364 align:middle line:84%
And there's nothing
discreet about these events.

01:21:37.364 --> 01:21:39.780 align:middle line:84%
These-- We're-- Everything is
intermingled with everything

01:21:39.780 --> 01:21:40.280 align:middle line:90%
else.

01:21:40.280 --> 01:21:42.602 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's important
to continue to repeat that.

01:21:42.602 --> 01:21:43.560 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: Oh, endlessly.

01:21:43.560 --> 01:21:44.976 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Non dualism
and the we are

01:21:44.976 --> 01:21:46.374 align:middle line:90%
one concept all go together.

01:21:46.374 --> 01:21:47.040 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: Exactly

01:21:47.040 --> 01:21:49.540 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And then the
fifth tenant being about--

01:21:49.540 --> 01:21:51.360 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: --cosmic conscience.

01:21:51.360 --> 01:21:53.100 align:middle line:84%
Well, cosmic conscience
relates to this.

01:21:53.100 --> 01:21:57.310 align:middle line:84%
Because what-- if live in the
world of your personal ego,

01:21:57.310 --> 01:21:59.887 align:middle line:84%
your fears and your desires
relate to yourself personally.

01:21:59.887 --> 01:22:00.970 align:middle line:90%
And everything's about me.

01:22:00.970 --> 01:22:01.590 align:middle line:90%
What's good for me?

01:22:01.590 --> 01:22:02.330 align:middle line:90%
What do I want?

01:22:02.330 --> 01:22:03.540 align:middle line:90%
What am I afraid of?

01:22:03.540 --> 01:22:04.290 align:middle line:90%
OK?

01:22:04.290 --> 01:22:07.010 align:middle line:84%
But when you have-- when
you awaken to evolution

01:22:07.010 --> 01:22:11.370 align:middle line:84%
and you realize that my ego is
just a small part of who I am,

01:22:11.370 --> 01:22:13.430 align:middle line:84%
and who I really
am is the ener--

01:22:13.430 --> 01:22:15.530 align:middle line:84%
is the singulari--
the singular energy

01:22:15.530 --> 01:22:17.280 align:middle line:84%
and intelligence that
created the universe

01:22:17.280 --> 01:22:19.540 align:middle line:84%
and is creating the universe,
is the creative force

01:22:19.540 --> 01:22:23.710 align:middle line:84%
in the universe of Eros-- I
am that awakening to itself

01:22:23.710 --> 01:22:27.600 align:middle line:84%
in the form of this body, this
mind, and this personality--

01:22:27.600 --> 01:22:30.960 align:middle line:84%
when you grasp that, experience
that at a very deep level,

01:22:30.960 --> 01:22:34.790 align:middle line:84%
you begin to feel a sense
of enormous care and concern

01:22:34.790 --> 01:22:36.580 align:middle line:90%
about where we're all going.

01:22:36.580 --> 01:22:38.950 align:middle line:84%
You begin to feel less
concerned about me

01:22:38.950 --> 01:22:41.157 align:middle line:84%
an infinitely more
concerned about we.

01:22:41.157 --> 01:22:42.490 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Is that the bottom line?

01:22:42.490 --> 01:22:43.130 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: Yes.

01:22:43.130 --> 01:22:43.630 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

01:22:43.630 --> 01:22:44.150 align:middle line:90%
Is that--

01:22:44.150 --> 01:22:45.390 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: That's the bottom line.

01:22:45.390 --> 01:22:46.480 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: --how it
all ties together?

01:22:46.480 --> 01:22:47.840 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, in the
way that I approach

01:22:47.840 --> 01:22:49.220 align:middle line:84%
it, the way we
get over ourselves

01:22:49.220 --> 01:22:52.045 align:middle line:84%
is by awakening to this
big-- this ultimate context

01:22:52.045 --> 01:22:55.890 align:middle line:84%
in which-- that we all
are part and parcel of.

01:22:55.890 --> 01:22:58.530 align:middle line:84%
And that's how I think we
can get over ourselves.

01:22:58.530 --> 01:23:03.370 align:middle line:84%
Because we're like-- So there's
a sense of care and concern

01:23:03.370 --> 01:23:05.660 align:middle line:84%
that we begin to-- We awaken
to a sense of care that

01:23:05.660 --> 01:23:06.520 align:middle line:90%
wasn't there before.

01:23:06.520 --> 01:23:09.140 align:middle line:84%
We suddenly care desperately
about where we're going.

01:23:09.140 --> 01:23:14.670 align:middle line:84%
And then that becomes our
life mode, our personality,

01:23:14.670 --> 01:23:17.180 align:middle line:84%
and our life mode
of-- become-- we--

01:23:17.180 --> 01:23:18.840 align:middle line:84%
the-- Our personality
begins to become

01:23:18.840 --> 01:23:21.820 align:middle line:84%
an expression of that
care for the future.

01:23:21.820 --> 01:23:23.550 align:middle line:84%
You know, in
evolutionary-- Evolution

01:23:23.550 --> 01:23:24.550 align:middle line:90%
is all about the future.

01:23:24.550 --> 01:23:25.950 align:middle line:84%
It's all about
where we're going.

01:23:25.950 --> 01:23:27.450 align:middle line:84%
Then your traditional
enlightenment,

01:23:27.450 --> 01:23:29.082 align:middle line:84%
which is very
popular still today,

01:23:29.082 --> 01:23:30.540 align:middle line:84%
it's all about
being in the moment,

01:23:30.540 --> 01:23:32.415 align:middle line:84%
being in the present
moment, be here and now.

01:23:32.415 --> 01:23:35.340 align:middle line:84%
And I'd say-- But in the new
evolutionary enlightenment,

01:23:35.340 --> 01:23:37.370 align:middle line:84%
it's not only about being
in the present moment,

01:23:37.370 --> 01:23:39.310 align:middle line:84%
it's all about
being very conscious

01:23:39.310 --> 01:23:41.790 align:middle line:84%
of the next moment,
where we're going.

01:23:41.790 --> 01:23:43.800 align:middle line:84%
Are we concerned about
where we're going?

01:23:43.800 --> 01:23:45.840 align:middle line:84%
Are we awake to,
conscious of-- are

01:23:45.840 --> 01:23:48.060 align:middle line:84%
we reaching for
that next moment?

01:23:48.060 --> 01:23:50.020 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So not so much
of being here now,

01:23:50.020 --> 01:23:52.730 align:middle line:84%
but being here now and the next
moment and the next moment.

01:23:52.730 --> 01:23:54.980 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: Well, it's a very
future-oriented liberation.

01:23:54.980 --> 01:23:56.374 align:middle line:90%


01:23:56.374 --> 01:23:57.790 align:middle line:84%
It's a very
future-oriented-- It's

01:23:57.790 --> 01:24:00.555 align:middle line:84%
when-- If you realized that
where we were going-- if you've

01:24:00.555 --> 01:24:01.930 align:middle line:84%
realized from a
moment that-- how

01:24:01.930 --> 01:24:03.890 align:middle line:84%
you can kind of
get a sense of it.

01:24:03.890 --> 01:24:07.380 align:middle line:84%
If you realize where the future
of the entire cosmos and then--

01:24:07.380 --> 01:24:09.580 align:middle line:84%
and every-- and all
of humanity depended

01:24:09.580 --> 01:24:12.380 align:middle line:84%
upon you as an
individual-- only you.

01:24:12.380 --> 01:24:13.855 align:middle line:90%


01:24:13.855 --> 01:24:17.304 align:middle line:84%
It's a thought experiment or
kind of a metaphysical fantasy,

01:24:17.304 --> 01:24:17.970 align:middle line:90%
not really true.

01:24:17.970 --> 01:24:20.630 align:middle line:84%
But imagine if it was true that
it was-- that our future was

01:24:20.630 --> 01:24:23.204 align:middle line:84%
dependent upon you, your
choices, your actions.

01:24:23.204 --> 01:24:25.120 align:middle line:84%
You'd suddenly feel a
great overwhelming sense

01:24:25.120 --> 01:24:25.880 align:middle line:90%
of responsibility.

01:24:25.880 --> 01:24:27.530 align:middle line:84%
Your personal concerns would
disappear, wouldn't they?

01:24:27.530 --> 01:24:28.240 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes, absolutely.

01:24:28.240 --> 01:24:28.980 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: That's what
I'm talking about.

01:24:28.980 --> 01:24:30.390 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Absolutely, yes.

01:24:30.390 --> 01:24:32.410 align:middle line:84%
So it's a chunking up,
basically, to our--

01:24:32.410 --> 01:24:34.520 align:middle line:84%
And so people will be
called to do things

01:24:34.520 --> 01:24:36.540 align:middle line:84%
like help children
in Afghanistan

01:24:36.540 --> 01:24:40.225 align:middle line:84%
or going to different
areas to be of service.

01:24:40.225 --> 01:24:41.315 align:middle line:90%


01:24:41.315 --> 01:24:42.440 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: But not only that.

01:24:42.440 --> 01:24:44.523 align:middle line:84%
And that's an important
distinction you're making.

01:24:44.523 --> 01:24:47.800 align:middle line:84%
Because traditionally,
in, for example,

01:24:47.800 --> 01:24:50.030 align:middle line:84%
in Christianity-- and
Christians really, I think,

01:24:50.030 --> 01:24:52.940 align:middle line:84%
of all the traditions, have done
better at this than anybody.

01:24:52.940 --> 01:24:56.030 align:middle line:84%
If you're a good Christian, you
express your love for Christ

01:24:56.030 --> 01:24:57.486 align:middle line:90%
through loving your neighbor.

01:24:57.486 --> 01:24:59.860 align:middle line:84%
And so you're going to see
more Christians in Afghanistan

01:24:59.860 --> 01:25:02.120 align:middle line:84%
and in Haiti and other
places than you're

01:25:02.120 --> 01:25:04.400 align:middle line:84%
going to see Buddhists
or Hindus or Jews

01:25:04.400 --> 01:25:06.160 align:middle line:84%
or anybody else,
interestingly enough.

01:25:06.160 --> 01:25:08.950 align:middle line:84%
But also the-- in
Buddhism there's

01:25:08.950 --> 01:25:12.240 align:middle line:84%
a whole notion in Mahayana
Buddhism of compassion.

01:25:12.240 --> 01:25:16.330 align:middle line:84%
Traditionally, compassion,
or the selfle-- or healing

01:25:16.330 --> 01:25:20.690 align:middle line:84%
the wounds of existence,
become the expression

01:25:20.690 --> 01:25:22.810 align:middle line:90%
of enlightenment in the world.

01:25:22.810 --> 01:25:24.537 align:middle line:84%
And that's
traditionally been true.

01:25:24.537 --> 01:25:25.370 align:middle line:90%
And it's still true.

01:25:25.370 --> 01:25:28.500 align:middle line:84%
The biggest gurus in India
now do enormous amounts

01:25:28.500 --> 01:25:29.659 align:middle line:90%
of social work.

01:25:29.659 --> 01:25:31.700 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Physically, not
just meditating about it,

01:25:31.700 --> 01:25:32.324 align:middle line:90%
but physically.

01:25:32.324 --> 01:25:35.490 align:middle line:84%
>>COHEN: No, no, well they
medi-- but their movements have

01:25:35.490 --> 01:25:38.370 align:middle line:84%
systems in place that do
enormous amounts of social work

01:25:38.370 --> 01:25:39.730 align:middle line:90%
that uplift the poor.

01:25:39.730 --> 01:25:41.640 align:middle line:84%
So-- But what I--
But the whole notion

01:25:41.640 --> 01:25:44.950 align:middle line:84%
of what it means to help in an
evolutionary context shifts.

01:25:44.950 --> 01:25:49.320 align:middle line:84%
Because what we're talking
about is healing woundedness

01:25:49.320 --> 01:25:51.210 align:middle line:84%
and healing the
very real-- dealing

01:25:51.210 --> 01:25:53.680 align:middle line:84%
with very many real problems
that we have in the world.

01:25:53.680 --> 01:25:56.537 align:middle line:84%
But there's another issue here,
which is where we're going.

01:25:56.537 --> 01:25:58.120 align:middle line:84%
And we also have to
have our attention

01:25:58.120 --> 01:26:01.020 align:middle line:84%
on that, which is giving
rise, as I've been saying,

01:26:01.020 --> 01:26:03.090 align:middle line:84%
to potentials and
possibilities and capacities

01:26:03.090 --> 01:26:04.380 align:middle line:90%
that don't exist yet.

01:26:04.380 --> 01:26:08.510 align:middle line:84%
So it's not-- So the future
is not only about healing.

01:26:08.510 --> 01:26:12.230 align:middle line:84%
There's another emerging
expression of compassion

01:26:12.230 --> 01:26:15.900 align:middle line:84%
which is all about creating
that which doesn't exist yet.

01:26:15.900 --> 01:26:17.366 align:middle line:90%


01:26:17.366 --> 01:26:18.990 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That right
there can be applied

01:26:18.990 --> 01:26:20.390 align:middle line:90%
to every area of your life.

01:26:20.390 --> 01:26:21.890 align:middle line:84%
That could be
applied to parenting.

01:26:21.890 --> 01:26:24.400 align:middle line:84%
That could be applied to
your vocation in life.

01:26:24.400 --> 01:26:26.740 align:middle line:84%
That could be applied
to your relationship.

01:26:26.740 --> 01:26:28.590 align:middle line:84%
It's giving existence
to something

01:26:28.590 --> 01:26:30.310 align:middle line:84%
that doesn't exist
yet and creating

01:26:30.310 --> 01:26:33.917 align:middle line:84%
from that space is a very
powerful place to be.

01:26:33.917 --> 01:26:34.750 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: Well, yeah.

01:26:34.750 --> 01:26:36.830 align:middle line:84%
But I mean, the
thing is that, Lisa,

01:26:36.830 --> 01:26:41.800 align:middle line:84%
that culture are shared
agreements and shared values.

01:26:41.800 --> 01:26:43.800 align:middle line:84%
So what culture doesn't
exist out there;

01:26:43.800 --> 01:26:47.930 align:middle line:84%
it exists-- When we agree about
what's most important in life

01:26:47.930 --> 01:26:50.624 align:middle line:84%
and about what's real, we
create culture together.

01:26:50.624 --> 01:26:52.540 align:middle line:84%
And so when we talk about
creating the future,

01:26:52.540 --> 01:26:55.760 align:middle line:84%
we're actually talking about
creating new shared agreements,

01:26:55.760 --> 01:26:56.710 align:middle line:90%
creating new values.

01:26:56.710 --> 01:26:57.740 align:middle line:84%
Because that's what
culture is going

01:26:57.740 --> 01:26:58.930 align:middle line:90%
to look like in the future.

01:26:58.930 --> 01:27:02.460 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's work that's
very urgent that we need.

01:27:02.460 --> 01:27:03.589 align:middle line:90%
Because where are we going?

01:27:03.589 --> 01:27:05.630 align:middle line:84%
Everybody is talking about
technology, of course,

01:27:05.630 --> 01:27:08.345 align:middle line:84%
as leading the w-- as
shaping culture now

01:27:08.345 --> 01:27:12.514 align:middle line:84%
and having a very big effect on
the way we're relating to life

01:27:12.514 --> 01:27:14.180 align:middle line:84%
or the way we're
relating to each other.

01:27:14.180 --> 01:27:17.300 align:middle line:84%
But technology is merely
the ways and means

01:27:17.300 --> 01:27:18.950 align:middle line:84%
in which we're
sharing information.

01:27:18.950 --> 01:27:20.980 align:middle line:84%
But it doesn't
affect our values.

01:27:20.980 --> 01:27:21.990 align:middle line:90%


01:27:21.990 --> 01:27:23.790 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't affect
our shared agreements

01:27:23.790 --> 01:27:24.760 align:middle line:90%
about what's important.

01:27:24.760 --> 01:27:27.170 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Unless we can infuse
our values into the technology.

01:27:27.170 --> 01:27:28.170 align:middle line:90%
>>COHEN: The new values.

01:27:28.170 --> 01:27:30.235 align:middle line:84%
But we have to
create them first.

01:27:30.235 --> 01:27:33.075 align:middle line:84%
And I think-- That's
the big work at hand.

01:27:33.075 --> 01:27:34.470 align:middle line:90%


01:27:34.470 --> 01:27:36.310 align:middle line:84%
